1
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:17,170
[ CLICKING ]

2
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:20,160
[ BEEPING ]

3
00:00:23,670 --> 00:00:26,170
<i>Woman: CHILDREN,
EXPERIENCE TELLS ME</i>

4
00:00:26,670 --> 00:00:30,180
<i>THAT SOME OF YOU WILL FORGET
THE LESSONS I HAVE TAUGHT.</i>

5
00:00:30,180 --> 00:00:32,680
No.

6
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:34,180
<i>THIS SUMMER,
TAKE TIME TO REFLECT</i>

7
00:00:34,180 --> 00:00:36,680
ON YOUR PAST YEAR
IN THE SECOND GRADE...

8
00:00:36,680 --> 00:00:38,190
[ COMPUTER GAME BEEPS ]
YES!

9
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:40,180
...AND HOW YOU CAN MAKE
THIRD GRADE BETTER.

10
00:00:40,190 --> 00:00:41,690
NO!

11
00:00:41,690 --> 00:00:46,190
MR. O'MALLEY,
DO YOU DISAGREE WITH ME?

12
00:00:46,190 --> 00:00:49,200
NO, SISTER LEONORA MARY.
I AGREE.

13
00:00:49,190 --> 00:00:50,690
[ CHILDREN GIGGLE ]

14
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:53,200
<i>Woman: PETE! <i>BOYS!</i>

15
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,700
<i>COME ON, LET'S GO!</i>

16
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,700
<i>MOM...</i>

17
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:57,710
YES, HONEY?

18
00:00:57,700 --> 00:00:59,700
I TOLD THEM TO BE READY
BY 9:20,

19
00:01:00,210 --> 00:01:01,710
BUT THEY JUST DON'T LISTEN.

20
00:01:03,710 --> 00:01:05,210
ANOTHER COMEBACK STOPPED!

21
00:01:05,210 --> 00:01:06,710
REGGIE JACKSON STINKS.

22
00:01:06,710 --> 00:01:07,720
<i>BOYS!</i>

23
00:01:07,710 --> 00:01:10,210
WE GOTTA GET GOING.
MOM'S GONNA FREAK.

24
00:01:10,220 --> 00:01:11,720
<i>GET DOWN HERE RIGHT NOW!</i>

25
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:13,720
<i>WELL, WHAT SHOULD WE
TELL HER?</i>

26
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:15,720
YOU COULDN'T FIND
YOUR BELT.

27
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:16,720
HOLD ON!

28
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:19,230
WHY AREN'T YOU
GOING TO CHURCH?

29
00:01:19,220 --> 00:01:21,220
WHAT ARE YOU,
A DETECTIVE?

30
00:01:21,730 --> 00:01:23,730
WHY AREN'T YOU
IN THE CAR?

31
00:01:23,730 --> 00:01:25,230
<i>COME ON, LET'S GO!
GOD DOESN'T WAIT!</i>

32
00:01:25,730 --> 00:01:27,740
<i>IT'S KILLING ME I CAN'T BE
WITH THEM AT CHURCH.</i>

33
00:01:28,230 --> 00:01:29,730
MY MOST CHERISHED MOMENTS

34
00:01:29,740 --> 00:01:31,740
HAVE BEEN WITH YOU KIDS
AT CHURCH.

35
00:01:31,740 --> 00:01:34,240
SCREAMING BRATS.

36
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,740
<i>WHY ARE YOU LATE?</i>

37
00:01:35,740 --> 00:01:37,750
PETE COULDN'T FIND
HIS BELT.

38
00:01:37,740 --> 00:01:40,240
MM-HMM.
WHY ARE YOU LATE?

39
00:01:40,250 --> 00:01:42,250
SEAMUS LOST MY BELT.

40
00:01:43,250 --> 00:01:45,750
[ BABY CRIES ]

41
00:01:45,750 --> 00:01:48,760
HEY...
<i>WHY DIDN'T YOU GUYS MAKE US
WAIT A LITTLE LONGER?</i>

42
00:01:48,750 --> 00:01:51,250
YOU KNOW HOW I HATE
BEING LATE FOR MASS.

43
00:01:51,260 --> 00:01:53,760
<i>KATIE, YOUR TOYS
ARE EVERYWHERE.</i>

44
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:56,260
YOU KNOW WHAT? GOD GIVES YOU
168 HOURS A WEEK.

45
00:01:56,260 --> 00:01:58,270
<i>YOU'D THINK YOU'D GIVE HIM
ONE BACK.</i>

46
00:01:58,260 --> 00:02:00,760
IS THAT TOO MUCH TO ASK?
[ SIGHS ]

47
00:02:01,270 --> 00:02:02,770
I'VE BEEN READY
FOR THREE HOURS.

48
00:02:03,270 --> 00:02:04,770
OH, SHUT UP,
YOU KISS ASS.

49
00:02:04,770 --> 00:02:07,280
COME HERE.

50
00:02:07,270 --> 00:02:08,270
COME HERE.
NO.

51
00:02:08,770 --> 00:02:10,770
COME HERE. HONEY,
I'M NOT GONNA HIT YOU.

52
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:13,780
I JUST WANT TO TELL YOU,
YOU SHOULDN'T TALK LIKE THAT.

53
00:02:13,780 --> 00:02:15,780
<i>WHY AM I THE ONLY ONE
THAT GETS HIT?</i>

54
00:02:15,780 --> 00:02:17,290
[ COMPUTER GAME BEEPS ]
TOUCHDOWN!

55
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,780
<i>I'M CRUSHING YOU AGAIN.</i>

56
00:02:18,780 --> 00:02:19,780
[ BABY CRYING ]

57
00:02:19,790 --> 00:02:21,290
HERE, THAT ONE, TOO.

58
00:02:21,290 --> 00:02:24,290
<i>MAYBE THE TEDDY BEAR
WILL SHUT HER UP.</i>

59
00:02:24,290 --> 00:02:26,790
I'M GONNA SHUT YOU UP,
TOO, YOU LITTLE JERK.

60
00:02:26,790 --> 00:02:27,800
"C."

61
00:02:27,790 --> 00:02:29,290
[ BEEPS ]

62
00:02:29,290 --> 00:02:30,790
[ CRYING CONTINUES ]

63
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:32,800
<i>Pete:
GROWING UP IRISH-CATHOLIC,</i>

64
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,800
<i>HEAVEN AND HELL
ARE TALKED ABOUT</i>

65
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,310
<i>AS IF THEY'RE
MY NEXT-DOOR NEIGHBORS.</i>

66
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:38,300
[ COMPUTER GAME BEEPS ]
<i>TOUCHDOWN!</i>

67
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,300
<i>AND MY MOM'S JOB...</i>

68
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:42,810
GODDAMN IT.
<i>...IS TO LOVINGLY GUIDE US
TOWARDS THE RIGHT PATH.</i>

69
00:02:42,810 --> 00:02:44,810
LORD'S NAME IN VAIN.
COME HERE. COME HERE, MISTER.

70
00:02:45,310 --> 00:02:47,820
AGH!
<i>DON'T YOU TALK LIKE THAT,
YOU LITTLE SON OF A BITCH.</i>

71
00:02:47,810 --> 00:02:49,810
<i>WE'RE ON OUR WAY TO A CHURCH,
FOR CHRIST'S SAKE.</i>

72
00:02:49,820 --> 00:02:51,820
MORNING.
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

73
00:02:51,820 --> 00:02:52,820
[ BELL TOLLING ]

74
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:54,820
OKAY.
ALL RIGHT, HONEY.

75
00:02:54,820 --> 00:02:56,820
OKAY, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

76
00:02:56,820 --> 00:02:58,330
[ SCREAMS, CRIES ]

77
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,320
ALL RIGHT.

78
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:01,820
HAPPY SUNDAY,
EVERYBODY.

79
00:03:01,830 --> 00:03:04,330
MORNING, SON.

80
00:03:07,330 --> 00:03:10,330
[ SCREAMING ]

81
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:14,840
OKAY.

82
00:03:22,350 --> 00:03:25,350
Thank you, dear.

83
00:03:25,350 --> 00:03:27,860
Watch him.

84
00:03:44,870 --> 00:03:46,370
Get in there.
You're going to confession.

85
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:51,880
<i>Right over here,
right here, right here.</i>

86
00:03:58,380 --> 00:04:00,880
<i>Pete: UNFORTUNATELY,
NOBODY KNOWS</i>

87
00:04:00,890 --> 00:04:02,390
<i>THE EXACT PATH TO HEAVEN.</i>

88
00:04:02,390 --> 00:04:05,890
<i>MY MOM SAYS
THAT'S WHY WE GO TO CHURCH --</i>

89
00:04:05,890 --> 00:04:08,400
<i>TO PRAY TO JESUS
FOR ANSWERS.</i>

90
00:04:08,390 --> 00:04:10,890
<i>BUT HE JUST HANGS THERE
SILENTLY,</i>

91
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:13,900
<i>LOOKING DOWN AT ME,
SEEING EVERYTHING.</i>

92
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:18,910
<i>THAT CAN'T BE GOOD.</i>

93
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:20,400
HEY, MOM...
YES, DEAR?

94
00:04:20,410 --> 00:04:21,910
YOU THINK DOING MY CHORES

95
00:04:21,910 --> 00:04:23,910
WILL BE ENOUGH TO KEEP ME
OUT OF HELL?

96
00:04:23,910 --> 00:04:25,910
WHAT'D YOU BREAK?

97
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:31,410
PETER EDWARD O'MALLEY,
LOOK AT ME, HONEY.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

98
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:35,920
I THINK THAT
SISTER LEONORA MARY THINKS
THAT I'M GOING TO HELL.

99
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,930
AND WHY DO YOU THINK
SHE THINKS THIS?

100
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:40,920
WELL, SHE SORT OF SAID IT
A LOT THIS YEAR.
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

101
00:04:41,430 --> 00:04:43,430
MAYBE YOU CAN DO SOMETHING
TO PROVE TO SISTER MARY

102
00:04:43,430 --> 00:04:46,430
THAT YOU'RE GOING STRAIGHT TO
HEAVEN -- DO SOMETHING GOOD.

103
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:47,940
<i>HELLO?
OH, HI, JACKIE.</i>

104
00:04:47,930 --> 00:04:49,930
WELL, WHAT CAN I DO
TO PROVE IT TO HER?

105
00:04:49,940 --> 00:04:51,940
HONEY, JUST BE YOURSELF,
OBEY THE NUNS,

106
00:04:51,940 --> 00:04:53,940
AND YOU'LL BE FINE, OKAY?
YOU'RE A GOOD BOY.

107
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:56,440
HELLO.
WELL, YOU KNOW HOW I FEEL.

108
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:58,950
<i>IF YOU CAN'T SAY SOMETHING
GOOD, YOU JUST DON'T SAY
ANYTHING.</i>

109
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:00,440
BUT, YOU KNOW,
SHE <i>IS KIND OF LOOSE.</i>

110
00:05:00,450 --> 00:05:03,950
HMM, WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF SISTER LEONORA MARY?

111
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:06,450
SISTER BIG BAGS?
SHE'S ALL RIGHT.

112
00:05:06,450 --> 00:05:08,960
A LOT EASIER
THAN SISTER GLORIA.

113
00:05:09,450 --> 00:05:10,450
WHY?

114
00:05:10,460 --> 00:05:12,960
SHE KEEPS TELLING ME
I'M GOING TO HELL.

115
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,460
YEAH.
SHE'S BIG ON HELL.

116
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:16,460
WELL, HOW CAN I PROVE TO HER
THAT I'M NOT?

117
00:05:16,460 --> 00:05:18,970
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
TOMORROW'S THE LAST DAY
OF SCHOOL.

118
00:05:19,460 --> 00:05:20,960
<i>I KNOW, BUT LET'S SAY
I WANTED TO.</i>

119
00:05:20,970 --> 00:05:22,470
HOW WOULD I DO THAT?

120
00:05:22,970 --> 00:05:24,970
WELL, IN RELIGION CLASS,

121
00:05:24,970 --> 00:05:26,470
I DID THIS REPORT
ON ST. PAUL.

122
00:05:26,470 --> 00:05:28,480
HE'S THIS GUY
THAT AFTER JESUS DIED,

123
00:05:28,470 --> 00:05:31,970
HE KEPT GOING AROUND
TRYING TO CONVERT PEOPLE
INTO CHRISTIANITY.

124
00:05:31,980 --> 00:05:33,480
<i>HE WAS ON A QUEST.</i>

125
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,480
CONVERT PEOPLE
THAT WEREN'T CATHOLIC?

126
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:37,490
YEAH, THERE WERE A LOT
<i>BACK THEN,</i>

127
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,480
LIKE THE JEWISH PEOPLE
AND THE ROMANS.

128
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:40,980
JEWISH PEOPLE?

129
00:05:41,490 --> 00:05:43,990
YEAH, CONVERTING JEWISH PEOPLE
<i>WAS MAJOR.</i>

130
00:05:43,990 --> 00:05:46,990
THE ROMANS...I DON'T KNOW,
MAYBE EVEN THE GREEKS.

131
00:05:46,990 --> 00:05:48,000
<i>EVERYONE.</i>

132
00:05:47,990 --> 00:05:49,990
DID IT WORK?
THEY MADE HIM A SAINT.

133
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,000
YOU THINK THEY MIGHT
MAKE ME A SAINT?

134
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,500
[ Chuckling ] YEAH,
THAT'D KEEP YOU OUT OF HELL.

135
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,010
BUT THEY ALREADY GOT
A ST. PETER.

136
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:00,500
[ BELL RINGS ]

137
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:02,010
SEE YOU AT CHURCH...

138
00:06:02,010 --> 00:06:04,010
AND NEXT YEAR
IN THE THIRD GRADE.

139
00:06:04,010 --> 00:06:05,510
YOU MAY GO.

140
00:06:05,510 --> 00:06:10,020
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

141
00:06:10,020 --> 00:06:13,020
MR. O'MALLEY, MAY I SPEAK
TO YOU FOR A MOMENT?

142
00:06:16,020 --> 00:06:18,530
YES, SISTER LEONORA MARY?

143
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:21,520
HOW MANY TIMES HAVE I HAD
TO PULL YOU BY YOUR EARS

144
00:06:21,530 --> 00:06:24,030
TO THE FRONT OF THE CLASS
AND GIVE YOU THE RULER?

145
00:06:26,530 --> 00:06:27,540
A LOT.

146
00:06:27,530 --> 00:06:31,530
PROBABLY TOO MANY TIMES,
<i>DON'T YOU THINK?</i>

147
00:06:31,540 --> 00:06:34,040
I DON'T ENJOY HAVING TO DO THAT,
YOU KNOW.

148
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:37,550
<i>I THINK THIS IS
AN IMPORTANT SUMMER FOR YOU.</i>

149
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,040
THIS IS THE SUMMER

150
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:43,040
WHERE YOU CAN CHOOSE TO KEEP
FOLLOWING THE DEVIL'S WAY

151
00:06:43,050 --> 00:06:46,050
OR CREATE A NEW PATH
TOWARDS JESUS.

152
00:06:46,050 --> 00:06:48,560
<i>NOW, WHICH PATH
DO YOU WANT TO TAKE?</i>

153
00:06:48,550 --> 00:06:49,550
THE JESUS PATH.

154
00:06:49,550 --> 00:06:51,050
GOOD.

155
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:53,060
I EXPECT TO SEE A DIFFERENCE
IN YOU NEXT YEAR.

156
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:55,060
<i>OH, YOU WILL,
SISTER LEONORA MARY.</i>

157
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:57,570
I'VE GOT A PLAN --
A QUEST.

158
00:06:57,560 --> 00:07:00,060
GOOD. YOU MAY GO.

159
00:07:00,070 --> 00:07:03,070
<i>ENJOY YOUR SUMMER.
I KNOW YOU WILL.</i>

160
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:06,070
OH, UM...DO YOU KNOW WHERE
I CAN FIND A TEMPLE?

161
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,590
FIRST GAME OF THE SUMMER,
PETE.

162
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:19,580
<i>COME ON, SEAMUS,
I'M STARTING MY QUEST.</i>

163
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:20,580
<i>Boy: WHO'S GOT THE BALL?!</i>

164
00:07:20,590 --> 00:07:22,590
HEY, KEVIN!

165
00:07:24,090 --> 00:07:26,090
SO YOU'RE ACTUALLY GOING
TO THE TEMPLE?

166
00:07:26,090 --> 00:07:28,100
YEAH.

167
00:07:28,090 --> 00:07:30,590
YOU KNOW, THIS WHOLE THING'S
KIND OF WEIRD --

168
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:35,100
<i>YOU GOING THERE...
THE QUEST.</i>

169
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:36,100
YEAH.

170
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:39,610
WELL, AT LEAST
YOU KNOW IT'S WEIRD.

171
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:42,100
SEE YA.

172
00:07:42,110 --> 00:07:45,110
<i>Man: WELL, KEEP UP
THE GOOD WORK, JASON.</i>

173
00:07:45,610 --> 00:07:46,610
<i>I WILL.</i>

174
00:07:46,610 --> 00:07:49,120
<i>YOU'RE GONNA MAKE YOUR PARENTS
VERY PROUD.</i>

175
00:07:49,110 --> 00:07:50,610
THANK YOU, RABBI JACOBSEN.

176
00:07:50,620 --> 00:07:51,620
SEE YOU IN A COUPLE DAYS.

177
00:07:51,620 --> 00:07:53,120
YES.
BYE-BYE, NOW.

178
00:08:00,130 --> 00:08:01,630
HOW YOU DOING TODAY?

179
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:03,630
I'M GREAT. THANKS.

180
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:06,130
GOOD.

181
00:08:06,130 --> 00:08:07,130
WHAT'S THAT THING

182
00:08:07,130 --> 00:08:09,640
THAT YOU HAVE
ON THE TOP OF YOUR HEAD?

183
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:11,630
OH, IT'S, UH, CALLED
A YARMULKE.

184
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:14,140
<i>IT DOESN'T REALLY
BLOCK THE SUN, DOES IT?</i>

185
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,640
NO.

186
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:19,150
UH, BUT IT DOES BLOCK
BALD SPOTS.

187
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:21,640
<i>WHOA.
IT CAN <i>COVER BALD SPOTS.</i>

188
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:24,150
MY OLD UNCLE JIM
COULD HAVE USED THAT.

189
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:26,150
[ Chuckling ] UH-HUH.

190
00:08:26,150 --> 00:08:30,660
SO, YOU, UH...CASING THE JOINT
FOR A HEIST?

191
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:32,660
WHAT?

192
00:08:32,660 --> 00:08:33,660
[ CHUCKLES ]

193
00:08:33,660 --> 00:08:35,660
WHAT CAN I DO YOU FOR?

194
00:08:35,660 --> 00:08:38,670
JEWISH PEOPLE GO HERE,
RIGHT?

195
00:08:38,660 --> 00:08:39,660
UH-HUH.

196
00:08:39,660 --> 00:08:41,160
<i>I'M TRYING TO SEE</i>

197
00:08:41,170 --> 00:08:44,170
IF I CAN HELP JEWISH PEOPLE
GET TO HEAVEN.

198
00:08:44,170 --> 00:08:45,670
AH, ONE NOBLE ENDEAVOR.

199
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:46,670
A QUEST.

200
00:08:46,670 --> 00:08:48,180
A NOBLE <i>QUEST.</i>

201
00:08:48,670 --> 00:08:51,170
HOW MAY I BE
OF ASSISTANCE?

202
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:53,680
I JUST WANTED TO CHECK OUT
THE TEMPLE,

203
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,180
BUT THERE'S NO BIKE RACK.

204
00:08:55,180 --> 00:08:57,180
TELL YOU WHAT -- WHY DON'T YOU
LET ME HELP YOU

205
00:08:57,180 --> 00:08:59,690
FIND A PLACE FOR THE BIKE,
AND I'LL SHOW YOU AROUND?

206
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:01,180
WELL, THANKS.

207
00:09:01,190 --> 00:09:04,190
AND THAT WAY, WHEN YOU
AND THE REST OF THE GANG
GET TOGETHER,

208
00:09:04,190 --> 00:09:05,690
YOU'LL KNOW
WHERE THE SAFE IS.

209
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:07,190
WHAT GANG AND WHAT SAFE?

210
00:09:07,190 --> 00:09:09,200
YOU KNOW, FOR THE HEIST.

211
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:14,700
<i>Pete: NO CROSS?</i>

212
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:16,200
<i>Rabbi:
UH, NO. NO CROSS.</i>

213
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,710
<i>I FIND THE CROSS
FUN TO LOOK AT.</i>

214
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:21,200
SOMETIMES I THINK ABOUT
CLIMBING UP THE WALL

215
00:09:21,210 --> 00:09:24,210
AND UNSCREWING THE SCREWS,
AND LETTING HIM GO.

216
00:09:24,210 --> 00:09:25,710
MASS GOES FASTER THAT WAY.

217
00:09:26,210 --> 00:09:27,210
UH-HUH.

218
00:09:27,210 --> 00:09:30,220
YOU SHOULD REALLY THINK
ABOUT PUTTING ONE IN HERE.

219
00:09:30,220 --> 00:09:33,220
I WILL GIVE THAT
SOME THOUGHT.

220
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:35,220
SO, WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

221
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:39,230
I'M THINKING THAT THIS IS
WHERE MY QUEST STARTS.

222
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:40,720
OKAY.

223
00:09:40,730 --> 00:09:43,230
WELL, IF I CAN BE OF ANY
ASSISTANCE, DON'T HESITATE.

224
00:09:43,230 --> 00:09:45,730
MY OFFICE IS RIGHT THROUGH
THOSE DOORS THERE.

225
00:09:45,730 --> 00:09:47,740
I'D SHOW YOU AROUND
A LITTLE BIT MORE,

226
00:09:48,230 --> 00:09:51,230
BUT I GOTTA GET BACK
TO MY FAMILY. I HAVE A --

227
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,240
YOU HAVE A FAMILY?

228
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:54,740
<i>YEAH.</i>

229
00:09:54,740 --> 00:09:57,240
WELL, THEN WHAT DO THEY
CALL YOU?

230
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:59,750
WELL, MY SON CALLS ME DAD,

231
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:03,240
AND MY CONGREGATION
CALLS ME RABBI...

232
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:04,750
RABBI JACOBSEN.

233
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:06,750
PETE. PETE O'MALLEY.

234
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:09,260
NICE TO MEET YOU,
RABBI JACOBSEN.

235
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,750
NICE TO MEET YOU,
PETE O'MALLEY.

236
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:13,260
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

237
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:16,760
OH, LOOK AT
ALL THESE LITTLE...

238
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:20,770
STOP MAKING UP
THESE STORIES.

239
00:10:20,770 --> 00:10:23,270
YOU'RE JUST LYING
THROUGH YOUR TEETH.

240
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:24,770
<i>DON'T LISTEN TO HIM.</i>

241
00:10:24,770 --> 00:10:27,270
I WAS LIKE, "HI, JULIE,"
AND SHE WAS LIKE, "HI, EDDIE."

242
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:28,780
<i>SHE DID NOT SAY THAT.</i>

243
00:10:28,770 --> 00:10:30,770
<i>OH, SHE SAID,
"HI, EDDIE..."</i>

244
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:33,780
<i>HEY. HEY, GET YOUR ELBOWS
OFF THE TABLE.</i>

245
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:36,280
<i>EDDIE, WHAT'S --
WHAT'S WITH YOUR HAIR?</i>

246
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:40,290
ALL MY FRIENDS LOVED IT.
<i>YOU, MY FRIEND, ARE GOING TO
THE BARBER COLLEGE THIS WEEK.</i>

247
00:10:40,290 --> 00:10:42,790
CAN I HAVE YOUR ATTENTION,
PLEASE?

248
00:10:42,790 --> 00:10:43,790
<i>I GOT SOMETHING TO SAY!</i>

249
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:45,790
WELL, I GUESS SO.

250
00:10:46,290 --> 00:10:48,300
THIS BETTER BE GOOD,
KATIE.

251
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:50,290
SO, TODAY, I PEDALED MY BIKE

252
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:52,800
ALL THE WAY DOWN
TO O'CONNOR'S HOUSE.

253
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:55,300
THEN, I PEDALED BACK,
AND IT WAS SUNNY.

254
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:56,800
AND IT WAS SUNNY.
[ LAUGHS ]

255
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:59,310
<i>SPEECH THERAPY FOR
THIS ONE -- MAYBE.</i>

256
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:00,800
<i>Margaret: HONEY...</i>

257
00:11:00,810 --> 00:11:02,310
<i>[ Sarcastically ]
THAT'S GREAT.
MAKE FUN OF HER.</i>

258
00:11:02,810 --> 00:11:04,810
DOES ANYBODY KNOW
WHAT A YARMULKE IS?

259
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:05,810
<i>YOU MEAN A BEANIE?</i>

260
00:11:06,310 --> 00:11:07,820
NO, IT'S NOT A BEANIE,
POP.

261
00:11:07,810 --> 00:11:09,810
IT'S, UH -- JEWISH PEOPLE
WEAR THEM, PETE.

262
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,320
IT'S -- IT'S RELIGIOUS.

263
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,320
IT'S THEIR TRADITIONAL
HEAD WEAR.

264
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:15,820
IT'S LIKE FEATHERS
FOR INDIANS.
EXACTLY.

265
00:11:15,820 --> 00:11:16,820
WELL, WHAT'S IT FOR?

266
00:11:16,820 --> 00:11:18,330
TO HIDE THEIR HORNS.

267
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:19,820
<i>THEY HAVE HORNS?</i>

268
00:11:20,330 --> 00:11:20,830
[ LAUGHS ]

269
00:11:21,330 --> 00:11:22,830
JOSEPH!
NO, THAT'S NOT RIGHT,

270
00:11:22,830 --> 00:11:25,330
AND NOBODY REPEATS THAT
OUT OF THIS HOUSE.

271
00:11:25,330 --> 00:11:27,330
<i>DO YOU HEAR ME?
WHO WANTS ICE CREAM?</i>

272
00:11:27,330 --> 00:11:28,840
I DO.
CHOCOLATE, PLEASE.

273
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:30,330
COME ON,
I NEED HELPERS.

274
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:31,340
VANILLA.
THANK YOU.

275
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:33,840
YOU'RE REQUESTING FLAVORS?
YOU'LL GET WHAT WE HAVE.

276
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:36,340
WE ALWAYS DO.
PETE, GET ME SOME --
SOME VANILLA.

277
00:11:36,340 --> 00:11:38,850
<i>SO, YOUR UNCLE CHARLIE
CAN GET YOU AN INTERVIEW</i>

278
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:40,340
AT THE CITY PLANNER'S OFFICE.

279
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:41,850
YEAH, WELL, UH,
NO, THANKS.

280
00:11:41,850 --> 00:11:44,350
<i>WELL, PATRICK, WHAT ABOUT
THE FIRE DEPARTMENT?</i>

281
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:46,350
<i>NO, NO, NO,
FORGET ABOUT THAT.</i>

282
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:48,360
THAT'S ALWAYS THERE
FOR HIM.

283
00:11:48,350 --> 00:11:50,350
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO?

284
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:51,860
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

285
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:52,860
WELL, UH, YOU KNOW,

286
00:11:52,860 --> 00:11:55,860
I'M STILL WAITING FOR THOSE
SCHOLARSHIPS TO COME THROUGH,

287
00:11:55,860 --> 00:11:57,870
AND UNTIL THEN, I'M
LIFEGUARDING, YOU KNOW.

288
00:11:57,860 --> 00:11:59,860
I'M MAKING MONEY
AND SAVING MONEY --

289
00:11:59,860 --> 00:12:01,860
LIFEGUARDING?
[ LAUGHS ]

290
00:12:01,870 --> 00:12:04,870
I RAISED A PROFESSIONAL
LIFEGUARDER IN CHICAGO.

291
00:12:05,370 --> 00:12:07,880
WORKS THREE MONTHS A YEAR,
RIGHT?

292
00:12:07,870 --> 00:12:09,370
DAD, IF YOU COULD SEE

293
00:12:09,370 --> 00:12:10,870
SHEILA MORAN
IN A BATHING SUIT,

294
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,880
YOU'D BE A LIFEGUARDER,
TOO, I PROMISE.

295
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:14,380
"OH, PATRICK, SAVE ME.

296
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:17,890
HELP! SAVE ME!
OH, GIVE ME A LITTLE KISS
ON THE CHEEK, BABY."

297
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:21,380
<i>PATRICK, FRANCIS DEMOS TOLD ME
SHEILA LIKES YOU.</i>

298
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:23,390
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS ASK HER OUT.

299
00:12:23,390 --> 00:12:25,890
DON'T LET HER OLD MAN
CATCH YOU.
NO KIDDING.

300
00:12:26,390 --> 00:12:28,400
DO WE HAVE TO TALK ABOUT
MY PERSONAL LIFE

301
00:12:28,390 --> 00:12:29,390
EVERY NIGHT AT DINNER?

302
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:30,890
[ LAUGHS ]

303
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:33,150
I THINK YOU LIKE HER,
SON.

304
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,900
[ BIRDS CHIRPING, CHILDREN
SHOUTING IN DISTANCE ]

305
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:41,400
COME IN.

306
00:12:41,410 --> 00:12:43,910
HEY, RABBI JACOBSEN.
IT'S ME -- PETE O'MALLEY.

307
00:12:43,910 --> 00:12:46,910
OH, YES, MR. O'MALLEY,
HAVE A SEAT. HOW ARE YOU?

308
00:12:46,910 --> 00:12:48,920
I'M GREAT. THANKS.

309
00:12:48,910 --> 00:12:50,410
I'M READY TO START
MY QUEST,

310
00:12:50,420 --> 00:12:52,920
BUT I THOUGHT I MIGHT NEED
YOUR PERMISSION FIRST.

311
00:12:53,420 --> 00:12:54,920
EXCELLENT IDEA.
WHAT ARE YOUR PLANS?

312
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:56,920
I WAS THINKING OF SETTING UP

313
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:59,430
THIS LEMONADE "FREE TRIP
TO HEAVEN" STAND.

314
00:12:59,420 --> 00:13:00,920
OF COURSE!

315
00:13:00,930 --> 00:13:04,930
THE OLD LEMONADE "FREE TRIP
TO HEAVEN" STAND.

316
00:13:04,930 --> 00:13:06,430
VERY ENTERPRISING.

317
00:13:06,430 --> 00:13:07,940
JEWISH PEOPLE LIKE
LEMONADE, RIGHT?

318
00:13:07,930 --> 00:13:08,930
<i>OH, SURE.</i>

319
00:13:09,430 --> 00:13:11,930
IN FACT, I THINK MOSES HAD
THE FIRST SETUP ON MOUNT SINAI.

320
00:13:11,940 --> 00:13:15,440
<i>I'M -- I'M JUST SETTING IT UP,
UH, AT THE FRONT DOOR.</i>

321
00:13:15,940 --> 00:13:17,950
OH, AND I'M NOT GONNA
CHARGE.

322
00:13:17,940 --> 00:13:20,440
WELL, IF YOU'RE NOT GONNA
CHARGE ANYTHING,

323
00:13:20,450 --> 00:13:22,450
PEOPLE WON'T TAKE YOU
SERIOUSLY.

324
00:13:22,450 --> 00:13:23,950
HOW ABOUT A NICKEL?

325
00:13:25,950 --> 00:13:26,950
ALL RIGHT.

326
00:13:26,950 --> 00:13:29,460
FINE,
DON'T CHARGE ANYONE.

327
00:13:29,450 --> 00:13:30,950
I'M SURE THAT'LL WORK.

328
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,960
I'LL LET YOU KNOW
HOW EVERYTHING GOES.

329
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:34,960
<i>APPRECIATE IT.</i>

330
00:13:35,460 --> 00:13:36,960
<i>UH, PETE...</i>

331
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:37,970
YEAH?

332
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,960
JEWISH PEOPLE DO BELIEVE
IN HEAVEN,

333
00:13:40,470 --> 00:13:42,470
JUST NOT THE SAME WAY
CHRISTIANS DO.

334
00:13:42,470 --> 00:13:44,970
OURS INVOLVES
A LITTLE MORE WAITING.

335
00:13:44,970 --> 00:13:49,480
WELL, MAYBE I COULD GET THE
PEOPLE WHO DON'T WANT TO WAIT.

336
00:13:49,470 --> 00:13:50,970
OKAY.

337
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:55,980
HERE YOU GO.

338
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:57,480
THANKS.

339
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:58,990
SEE YOU LATER.

340
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:12,000
[ BELL DINGS ]

341
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,500
[ DISTANT TALKING ]

342
00:14:26,010 --> 00:14:27,510
AH, MR. O'MALLEY.

343
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:31,020
JUST REMEMBER ROME
WASN'T BUILT IN A DAY.

344
00:14:31,020 --> 00:14:34,020
HOW DO YOU MAKE
ANY MONEY HERE?

345
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:37,020
I'M FREE,
AND I STILL HAVE NOBODY.

346
00:14:37,020 --> 00:14:38,530
I ENVY YOUR YOUTH.

347
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:41,020
YOU'LL DO BETTER
TOMORROW.

348
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:43,030
WELL, IT'S LATE TODAY,
THOUGH,

349
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:45,530
SO WHY DON'T I HELP YOU STORE
YOUR OFFICE?

350
00:14:45,530 --> 00:14:48,540
WE'LL PUT HER RIGHT INSIDE
THE SYNAGOGUE DOOR THERE --

351
00:14:48,530 --> 00:14:49,530
FOR FREE, OF COURSE.

352
00:14:49,530 --> 00:14:51,530
YOU KNOW, YOU AND I

353
00:14:51,540 --> 00:14:54,540
SEEM TO BE THE ONLY TWO
ON THIS BLOCK

354
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:57,040
THAT CARE ABOUT
FREE STUFF.

355
00:14:57,040 --> 00:15:00,050
WELL, THAT'S BECAUSE
WE REALIZE

356
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:03,040
WHAT WE HAVE TO OFFER
YOU CAN'T BUY.

357
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:06,050
EITHER THAT OR
YOUR LEMONADE STINKS.

358
00:15:06,050 --> 00:15:08,060
IS THAT A POSSIBILITY?

359
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:11,050
DON'T TELL MOM WE CHARGED CANDY
AT THE PHARMACY.

360
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:12,060
OKAY, I WON'T.

361
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:15,060
HEY, YOU WANT TO PLAY
SOME BALL TOMORROW?

362
00:15:15,060 --> 00:15:16,560
NO, I DON'T THINK I CAN.

363
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:18,570
I'M GOING TO
THE SYNAGOGUE AGAIN.

364
00:15:19,060 --> 00:15:20,060
[ VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES ]

365
00:15:20,060 --> 00:15:21,560
<i>DOOR-TO-DOOR SERVICE.</i>

366
00:15:21,570 --> 00:15:24,070
<i>IT'S A LOT TO ASK
FROM A PART-TIME SECRETARY.</i>

367
00:15:24,070 --> 00:15:26,570
RABBI JACOBSEN,
YOU'VE RECEIVED SIX MESSAGES.

368
00:15:26,570 --> 00:15:28,080
OH, YEAH?

369
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:31,070
LISTEN, WHATEVER WE'RE PAYING
YOU, IT'S NOT ENOUGH,

370
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:34,080
NOT IF YOU'RE GONNA INSIST
ON GIVING ME CURBSIDE SERVICE.

371
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,080
WHAT IS THIS?

372
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:37,580
MEMBERS OF THE CONGREGATION
DON'T SEEM TO THINK

373
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:40,580
THIS LEMONADE STAND
IS SUCH A LAUGHING MATTER.

374
00:15:40,590 --> 00:15:42,090
IT'S AGAINST JUDAISM.

375
00:15:42,090 --> 00:15:44,590
I'LL TELL YOU SOMETHING
ABOUT THIS CONGREGATION --

376
00:15:44,590 --> 00:15:46,590
THEY BARELY NOTICE
THIS SYNAGOGUE IS HERE

377
00:15:47,090 --> 00:15:48,600
UNLESS IT'S
THE HIGH HOLIDAYS.

378
00:15:48,590 --> 00:15:50,590
ALL HE'S DOING IS
ASKING PEOPLE TO THINK.

379
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:53,100
AND YOU'LL NOTICE,
WHEN YOU ASK PEOPLE TO THINK,

380
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:55,600
THAT'S WHEN THEY START
COMPLAINING.

381
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,600
BUT HE'S ADVERTISING
CHRISTIANITY.

382
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,610
NO, HE'S ADVERTISING
THOUGHT.

383
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:02,100
HE'S ASKING PEOPLE TO HAVE
A FREE CUP OF LEMONADE

384
00:16:02,110 --> 00:16:05,110
AND MAYBE GAIN SOME INSIGHT
ABOUT HOW TO GET INTO HEAVEN.

385
00:16:05,110 --> 00:16:08,120
IF THAT GOES AGAINST
PEOPLE'S WISHES, SO BE IT.

386
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:09,110
YOU KNOW WHAT I WISH?

387
00:16:09,110 --> 00:16:11,110
I WISH THERE WERE
A THOUSAND PETES

388
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:13,620
SETTING UP STANDS
ALL UP AND DOWN THE STREET.

389
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:16,120
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU LIKE STIRRING THINGS UP.

390
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:19,130
YEAH. MY GENERATION,
THEY'RE CRAZY.

391
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:22,120
LUCKILY, YOUR LOVELY WIFE
IS RAISING DANIEL.

392
00:16:22,130 --> 00:16:24,630
THAT IS A GOOD THING,
ISN'T IT?

393
00:16:24,630 --> 00:16:27,630
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

394
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:42,140
<i>Margaret:
SEAMUS, GET DOWN HERE!</i>

395
00:16:42,150 --> 00:16:45,150
<i>WHAT ARE YOU DOING
OUT OF THE TUB?</i>

396
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:47,150
<i>GET BACK IN THERE.</i>

397
00:16:49,650 --> 00:16:52,650
I DON'T THINK THIS QUEST THING
IS GONNA WORK.

398
00:16:52,660 --> 00:16:55,160
YOU'RE MISSING
SOME GREAT BASEBALL.

399
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:58,670
MULDOON SAYS HE'LL TRADE ME
AN ERNIE BANKS FOR A PETE ROSE.

400
00:16:58,660 --> 00:16:59,660
DO IT.

401
00:16:59,660 --> 00:17:01,160
TRADE FOR A CUB?

402
00:17:01,170 --> 00:17:03,170
IT'S NOT ABOUT
WHO YOU ROOT FOR.

403
00:17:03,170 --> 00:17:04,670
IT'S BUSINESS.

404
00:17:04,670 --> 00:17:06,670
BANKS IS GONNA BE
A HALL-OF-FAMER.

405
00:17:06,670 --> 00:17:08,680
WHO KNOWS ABOUT PETE ROSE?

406
00:17:08,670 --> 00:17:11,170
HEY, THERE'S THE RABBI
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT.

407
00:17:11,180 --> 00:17:12,180
[ SIREN WAILING ]

408
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:15,180
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER,
TIRES SQUEAL ]

409
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:17,180
I WONDER WHERE THE FIRE IS.

410
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:18,690
LET'S GO.

411
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:20,680
[ SIREN APPROACHING ]

412
00:17:20,690 --> 00:17:23,190
[ HORN HONKS ]

413
00:17:23,190 --> 00:17:25,190
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

414
00:17:25,190 --> 00:17:26,690
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

415
00:17:26,690 --> 00:17:28,200
<i>RIGHT HERE!</i>

416
00:17:28,190 --> 00:17:29,190
<i>THE WATER!</i>

417
00:17:29,190 --> 00:17:31,190
<i>OVER HERE!</i>

418
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,200
<i>TAKE IT EASY, SIR.</i>

419
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,700
THAT'S MY HOUSE.
THAT'S MY HOUSE!

420
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:36,200
I'M SORRY.
YOU CAN'T GO IN THERE.

421
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:38,210
MY SON'S IN THERE!
MY SON'S IN THERE!

422
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,700
WHERE IS HE AT?
WHERE IS HE AT?

423
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,700
<i>UPSTAIRS IN THE BACK!
THERE'S A WOMAN, TOO!</i>

424
00:17:41,710 --> 00:17:43,210
<i>DANNY!</i>

425
00:17:43,210 --> 00:17:45,210
COME ON, LET'S GO.

426
00:17:45,210 --> 00:17:47,210
WHERE'S DANNY?!
DANNY!
HONEY.

427
00:17:47,210 --> 00:17:49,220
<i>HE'S IN THE BACK!
HE'S IN THE BACK!</i>

428
00:17:49,210 --> 00:17:50,710
<i>[ Crying ] DANNY! DANNY!</i>

429
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:52,720
<i>HE'S IN THE BACK.</i>

430
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:54,720
[ SHOUTING CONTINUES ]

431
00:17:55,220 --> 00:17:57,220
<i>THEY'RE GONNA GET HIM.</i>

432
00:17:57,220 --> 00:18:00,230
HE'S IN THE BACK.

433
00:18:02,230 --> 00:18:03,230
[ CRYING ]

434
00:18:03,230 --> 00:18:05,230
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
THEY'RE GONNA GET HIM.

435
00:18:08,230 --> 00:18:09,730
THEY'RE GONNA GET HIM.

436
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:15,740
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

437
00:18:15,740 --> 00:18:17,240
YOU'RE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT,
OKAY?

438
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:18,750
YOU'RE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

439
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:20,740
HIS LEGS ARE MOVING.
HE'S GOTTA BE OKAY.

440
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:23,750
<i>DANNY! DANNY!
HE'S ALL RIGHT, YEAH?</i>

441
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:25,250
GET SOME OXYGEN ON HIM!

442
00:18:25,250 --> 00:18:29,260
OKAY, THERE'S A WOMAN INSIDE --
<i>ESTHER -- UPSTAIRS!</i>

443
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:32,250
SAME PLACE!
IT'S GOTTA BE THE SAME PLACE!

444
00:18:32,260 --> 00:18:33,760
NO, WE'RE GOING BACK.

445
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:35,260
JOE, IT'S TOO HOT.

446
00:18:35,260 --> 00:18:38,270
LET GO OF ME!
KEEP YOUR HANDS OFF ME!

447
00:18:38,260 --> 00:18:40,260
OH!

448
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:42,260
[ FIRE CRACKLING ]

449
00:18:42,270 --> 00:18:44,770
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

450
00:18:44,770 --> 00:18:46,270
I'M ALL RIGHT.
YOU ALL RIGHT?

451
00:18:46,270 --> 00:18:47,270
YEAH, YEAH, I'M FINE.

452
00:18:47,270 --> 00:18:49,280
ALL RIGHT, WE GOTTA GET BACK
AT THIS.

453
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:52,270
<i>THERE'S STILL A LADY
IN THERE, GUYS.</i>

454
00:18:52,280 --> 00:18:53,780
<i>JOE, IT'S TOO HOT!</i>

455
00:19:00,790 --> 00:19:03,790
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

456
00:19:06,290 --> 00:19:08,800
[ SIGHS ]

457
00:19:08,790 --> 00:19:10,290
HOW'S THE KID DOING?

458
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,300
HE'S GOOD.
YEAH?

459
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:16,800
<i>ALL RIGHT?</i>

460
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,310
DAD! DAD!

461
00:19:21,810 --> 00:19:23,810
<i>SEAMUS.</i>

462
00:19:28,810 --> 00:19:31,310
HOW MANY TIMES HAVE I TOLD YOU
NOT TO CHASE FIRE ENGINES?

463
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:33,820
<i>AND YOU BROUGHT
YOUR LITTLE BROTHER?</i>

464
00:19:33,820 --> 00:19:35,820
<i>HOW MANY TIMES
HAVE I TOLD YOU?</i>

465
00:19:35,820 --> 00:19:37,820
<i>YOU KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON
HERE, HUH?</i>

466
00:19:37,820 --> 00:19:40,330
GET YOUR CAN HOME
RIGHT NOW.

467
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:44,320
STAY THERE UNTIL
I GET BACK.

468
00:19:55,340 --> 00:19:57,340
SORRY, MA'AM.

469
00:19:57,340 --> 00:19:58,850
<i>THE FIRE WAS HUGE.</i>

470
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:00,340
IT WAS REALLY BIG.

471
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:01,840
MM-HMM.

472
00:20:01,850 --> 00:20:04,850
I WONDER
WHO THAT KID WAS.

473
00:20:04,850 --> 00:20:06,850
[ WHISTLES ]

474
00:20:09,350 --> 00:20:13,350
HOW MANY TIMES HAVE I TOLD
YOU BOYS, HUH?

475
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:17,860
YOU DON'T CHASE FIRES.
YOU RUN AWAY FROM THEM.

476
00:20:17,860 --> 00:20:20,370
YOU KNOW A LADY DIED
IN THAT FIRE TODAY?

477
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:21,360
WHO?

478
00:20:21,370 --> 00:20:24,370
AN OLDER LADY WHO WAS
BABYSITTING THE RABBI'S KID.

479
00:20:24,370 --> 00:20:26,370
SHE DIED.

480
00:20:31,380 --> 00:20:34,380
WHAT WERE YOU DOING
IN THAT NEIGHBORHOOD ANYWAY?

481
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:36,880
HUH?

482
00:20:37,380 --> 00:20:38,890
WHAT, A COUPLE OF MUTES?

483
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:41,380
ALL RIGHT, FINE.
YOU'RE BOTH GROUNDED.

484
00:20:41,390 --> 00:20:43,390
YOU DO NOT LEAVE
THIS BLOCK.

485
00:20:43,390 --> 00:20:46,890
IF I FIND OUT EITHER ONE
OF YOU LEFT THIS BLOCK,

486
00:20:46,890 --> 00:20:48,400
YOU WILL GET A SPANKIN'

487
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:51,390
THAT YOU WILL STILL FEEL
ON YOUR 16th BIRTHDAY.

488
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:52,900
BUT THE BASEBALL FIELD...

489
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,900
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

490
00:20:56,150 --> 00:20:58,240
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]],

491
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:15,260
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING UP?

492
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:16,250
<i>HUH?</i>

493
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:18,750
I COULDN'T SLEEP.

494
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:25,270
DAD, SEAMUS WAS
ONLY IN THE AREA

495
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:28,260
BECAUSE HE WAS
CHECKING UP ON ME.

496
00:21:30,770 --> 00:21:33,270
SEE, I'M -- I'M ON MY QUEST
TO MEET A JEWISH PERSON

497
00:21:33,770 --> 00:21:34,780
AND HELP THEM GET TO HEAVEN.

498
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:36,770
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING
ABOUT?

499
00:21:36,770 --> 00:21:40,270
I DON'T EVEN THINK JEWISH PEOPLE
BELIEVE IN HEAVEN THE WAY
YOU AND I DO.

500
00:21:40,280 --> 00:21:41,280
<i>I ASKED MOM,</i>

501
00:21:41,780 --> 00:21:44,280
AND SHE SAID THEY COULD BE
CONVERTED THROUGH JESUS.

502
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:48,290
<i>WELL, I ALSO ASKED
FATHER KELLY IN RELIGION CLASS.</i>

503
00:21:48,290 --> 00:21:50,790
HE SAID IT'S THE ROLE
OF A GOOD CHRISTIAN.

504
00:21:50,790 --> 00:21:51,790
HE SAID THAT?

505
00:21:51,790 --> 00:21:52,790
<i>MM-HMM.</i>

506
00:21:53,290 --> 00:21:54,290
<i>SO, ANYWAYS,</i>

507
00:21:54,290 --> 00:21:57,300
I'VE BEEN GOING OVER TO
THE SYNAGOGUE ON GREENWOOD.

508
00:21:57,300 --> 00:21:59,800
<i>YOU'VE BEEN GOING OVER
TO THAT SYNAGOGUE?</i>

509
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:02,300
YEAH, I'VE BEEN LOOKING
FOR JEWISH PEOPLE THERE.

510
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:04,810
<i>YEAH, ANY JEWS OVER THERE?
YEAH, I MET RABBI JACOBSEN.</i>

511
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,300
HE'S LIKE A PRIEST
BUT NOT AS SCARY.

512
00:22:07,810 --> 00:22:08,810
<i>HE'S REALLY NICE.</i>

513
00:22:08,810 --> 00:22:09,810
MM-HMM.

514
00:22:09,810 --> 00:22:11,310
HOW OLD ARE YOU?

515
00:22:11,310 --> 00:22:13,310
<i>8...AND 1/2.</i>

516
00:22:13,310 --> 00:22:15,320
YOU SHOULD BE WORRIED
ABOUT BASEBALL

517
00:22:15,310 --> 00:22:18,310
AND GOING TO THE SWIMMING POOL
AND BEING ASLEEP AT 9:00.

518
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:21,320
THAT'S ALL YOU SHOULD BE
WORRIED ABOUT, ALL RIGHT?

519
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:24,320
DON'T GO OVER TO THAT SYNAGOGUE
<i>ANYMORE, ALL RIGHT?</i>

520
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:25,830
YOU GO TO CHURCH,

521
00:22:25,820 --> 00:22:28,320
YOU LET THE JEWISH PEOPLE
TAKE CARE OF THEMSELVES.

522
00:22:28,830 --> 00:22:29,830
BUT I'M ON MY QUEST.

523
00:22:29,830 --> 00:22:31,830
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

524
00:22:31,830 --> 00:22:35,340
<i>DON'T TRY TO CHANGE
THE WORLD AT 8 1/2,</i>

525
00:22:35,330 --> 00:22:36,830
<i>ALL RIGHT?</i>

526
00:22:36,830 --> 00:22:38,830
<i>HEY, LOOK AT ME.</i>

527
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:41,840
GO TO BED.

528
00:22:45,340 --> 00:22:46,340
<i>HEY, PETE...</i>

529
00:22:46,340 --> 00:22:47,840
YEAH?

530
00:22:47,850 --> 00:22:49,350
GOOD NIGHT.

531
00:22:49,350 --> 00:22:51,350
GOOD NIGHT, DAD.

532
00:22:53,850 --> 00:22:56,860
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

533
00:22:58,860 --> 00:23:01,360
YOU KNOW, JOE, I CAN'T RAISE
THESE KIDS ALONE.

534
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:04,360
[ SIGHS ]

535
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:05,870
I'VE GAINED TOO MUCH WEIGHT

536
00:23:05,860 --> 00:23:08,360
TO FIND A NEW HUSBAND
AT THIS POINT.

537
00:23:08,370 --> 00:23:09,370
SO YOU'RE MY OPTION.

538
00:23:09,370 --> 00:23:12,370
IF YOU WERE SKINNIER
WHEN WE MET,

539
00:23:12,370 --> 00:23:15,380
THEN I SURE AS HELL
DON'T REMEMBER.

540
00:23:15,370 --> 00:23:17,370
AND NO WAY I LIKED IT.

541
00:23:17,380 --> 00:23:19,880
I LIKE SOMETHING
TO HOLD ONTO.

542
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:21,380
[ GROANS ] WELL, THEN...

543
00:23:21,380 --> 00:23:23,880
GO HOLD ONTO SOMETHING,
HONEY,

544
00:23:24,380 --> 00:23:26,890
BECAUSE SEX IS
NOT A CONVERSATION.

545
00:23:31,890 --> 00:23:34,390
DO YOU KNOW PETE IS GOING OVER
TO A SYNAGOGUE,

546
00:23:34,890 --> 00:23:36,890
TRYING TO CONVERT
JEWISH PEOPLE?

547
00:23:36,890 --> 00:23:37,890
[ LAUGHS ]

548
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:41,400
WHAT? I'M NOT FINDING THAT
AS FUNNY.

549
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:42,900
HONEY, HE'S A LITTLE BOY.

550
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:45,910
HE'S SEARCHING FOR MEANING
IN HIS LIFE, WHATEVER.

551
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:46,900
WHAT MEANING?

552
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:48,900
BASEBALL SHOULD BE
THE ONLY MEANING

553
00:23:48,910 --> 00:23:52,410
IN AN 8-YEAR-OLD'S LIFE.

554
00:23:52,410 --> 00:23:54,410
SOME KIDS ARE JUST DESTINED
FOR GREATER THINGS.

555
00:23:54,410 --> 00:23:56,420
SOUNDS LIKE HE'S LOOKING
TO GET HIS ASS KICKED.

556
00:23:56,410 --> 00:23:59,410
I TOLD HIM NOT TO GO OVER THERE,
AND DON'T YOU LET HIM
GO OVER THERE EITHER.

557
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:02,420
"I DON'T WANT YOU
TO LET HIM GO OVER THERE."

558
00:24:02,420 --> 00:24:05,430
HONEY, I CAN'T WATCH THEM
ALL DAY LONG, EVERY ONE OF THEM.

559
00:24:05,420 --> 00:24:08,920
COME ON, MOLLY'S A BABY.
SHE NEEDS MY CONSTANT ATTENTION.

560
00:24:08,930 --> 00:24:11,430
PETE GOES OUT IN THE MORNING,
HE COMES BACK, HE'S ALL CLEAN,

561
00:24:11,930 --> 00:24:14,430
NOBODY EVER CALLS TO SAY
HE'S BEEN IN ANY TROUBLE,

562
00:24:14,430 --> 00:24:15,440
I THINK I'M DOING ALL RIGHT.

563
00:24:15,930 --> 00:24:16,930
OH, THAT'S PARENTING 101.

564
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:19,440
HE'S CLEAN, AND
NOBODY SAYS HE'S TROUBLE.

565
00:24:19,940 --> 00:24:22,940
WHAT AM I GONNA HAVE TO DO,
RAISE THE KIDS <i>AND WORK?</i>

566
00:24:22,940 --> 00:24:23,940
DON'T START, JOE.

567
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:28,450
THAT IS JUST THE TERRITORY
YOU DON'T WANT TO GET INTO.

568
00:24:28,450 --> 00:24:30,450
HEY...

569
00:24:30,450 --> 00:24:32,450
<i>HMM?</i>

570
00:24:32,450 --> 00:24:33,950
<i>OH, NO.</i>

571
00:24:33,950 --> 00:24:37,960
HEY, IF WE WERE TO MAKE
A CHILD --

572
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:42,460
LET'S SAY WE WERE TO BRING
ANOTHER CHILD INTO THE WORLD

573
00:24:42,460 --> 00:24:43,460
RIGHT NOW --

574
00:24:43,460 --> 00:24:46,470
I PROMISE YOU
HE'D BE CLEAN,

575
00:24:46,460 --> 00:24:49,460
AND HE WOULDN'T BE
ANY TROUBLE.

576
00:24:53,470 --> 00:24:56,980
HONEY, YOU CAN'T JUST CLIMB
ON TOP OF ME,
FOR GOODNESS' SAKE.

577
00:24:56,970 --> 00:25:00,470
IF IT'S MY WOMB
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR,
CHECK THE BOTTOM OF THE BED,

578
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:02,480
'CAUSE I WAS DUSTING
AROUND THERE TODAY.

579
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:03,480
I THINK IT FELL OUT.

580
00:25:03,930 --> 00:25:06,990
[ VEHICLE PASSES BY,
DOG BARKS ]

581
00:25:06,980 --> 00:25:08,480
HEY, THAT'S GIN.

582
00:25:08,490 --> 00:25:09,990
WHAT?

583
00:25:09,990 --> 00:25:11,490
<i>YOU SHOULD BE A GARBAGEMAN</i>

584
00:25:11,990 --> 00:25:13,990
THE WAY YOU PICK UP
EVERY CARD I THROW DOWN.

585
00:25:13,990 --> 00:25:15,500
<i>YOU DO THAT TO PISS ME OFF?</i>

586
00:25:15,490 --> 00:25:16,990
NO, I DO IT TO WIN.

587
00:25:16,990 --> 00:25:18,990
WELL, AND TO PISS YOU OFF
A LITTLE.

588
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:22,000
<i>NOW, LET'S SEE --
500 TO 220...</i>

589
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:24,000
<i>AT, UH, WHAT,
A NICKEL A POINT.</i>

590
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:26,510
[ Irish accent ] THAT'S,
UH, 14 BUCKS YOU OWE ME,

591
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:28,000
LIEUTENANT O'MALLEY.

592
00:25:28,010 --> 00:25:29,010
HEY.

593
00:25:29,010 --> 00:25:31,010
GENTLEMEN.

594
00:25:31,010 --> 00:25:34,510
MY, UH, WIFE, SON, AND I
WANTED TO THANK YOU FOR
YOUR BRAVERY AND KINDNESS.

595
00:25:34,510 --> 00:25:36,520
THANK YOU.

596
00:25:37,010 --> 00:25:38,510
UH, HEY, YOU'RE WELCOME.

597
00:25:38,520 --> 00:25:39,520
RABBI, JOE O'MALLEY.

598
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:41,520
ON BEHALF OF MYSELF
AND ALL THE GUYS,

599
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:43,520
WE JUST WANT TO SAY WE'RE
REAL SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS.

600
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:45,030
<i>THANK YOU.</i>

601
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:47,020
UH, ESTHER LIVED
A VERY GOOD LIFE.

602
00:25:47,020 --> 00:25:50,020
SHE RAN MY SYNAGOGUE
LIKE AN ARMY BATTALION.

603
00:25:50,030 --> 00:25:51,030
OH, YEAH?

604
00:25:51,530 --> 00:25:54,030
UH, MY WIFE BELIEVES
THE BEST WAY TO THANK SOMEONE

605
00:25:54,030 --> 00:25:55,540
IS THROUGH THEIR STOMACH.

606
00:25:55,530 --> 00:25:57,530
SO SHE'S MADE SOME LASAGNA
FOR ALL OF YOU.

607
00:25:57,540 --> 00:25:58,540
IT'S REAL GOOD.

608
00:25:58,540 --> 00:26:00,540
<i>I'LL BET IT IS.
I'LL BET IT IS.</i>

609
00:26:00,540 --> 00:26:02,540
<i>YOU KNOW,
SHE SHOULDN'T HAVE.</i>

610
00:26:02,540 --> 00:26:05,550
<i>I MEAN, MY GUYS, UH,
THEY LOVE A GOOD MEAL,
ESPECIALLY THAT ONE,</i>

611
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:09,040
<i>BUT, UH, REALLY, HONESTLY,
WE'RE JUST DOING OUR JOB.</i>

612
00:26:09,050 --> 00:26:10,550
WELL, IT'S A HEROIC JOB
YOU DO,

613
00:26:10,550 --> 00:26:13,050
AND SHE WANTED TO THANK YOU
PERSONALLY,

614
00:26:13,050 --> 00:26:14,050
AND I'M SURE MY SYNAGOGUE'S

615
00:26:14,550 --> 00:26:16,060
GONNA WANT TO THANK YOU
FORMALLY.

616
00:26:16,050 --> 00:26:17,050
OH, YEAH.

617
00:26:17,050 --> 00:26:18,550
<i>Man: CHECK THIS OUT.</i>

618
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:21,560
IT TAKES TWO GUYS TO HOLD
THIS THING TO FIRE.

619
00:26:22,060 --> 00:26:25,070
<i>IN THE JEWISH TRADITION,
WE, UH, SIT SHIVA.</i>

620
00:26:25,060 --> 00:26:27,560
IT'S FOR THE MOURNERS
OF THE DECEASED.

621
00:26:27,570 --> 00:26:30,570
YEAH, YEAH, WE GOT SOMETHING
SIMILAR CALLED A WAKE.

622
00:26:30,570 --> 00:26:32,070
<i>RIGHT.
IT'S LIKE A WAKE.</i>

623
00:26:32,070 --> 00:26:33,570
SORT OF.

624
00:26:33,570 --> 00:26:35,580
ANYWAYS,
I KNOW YOU'RE BUSY,

625
00:26:35,570 --> 00:26:39,070
BUT I MENTION IT 'CAUSE
I'D BE HONORED IF YOU'D STOP BY

626
00:26:39,080 --> 00:26:42,580
AND SIT WITH MY FAMILY AND
FRIENDS FOR A FEW MINUTES.

627
00:26:42,580 --> 00:26:46,090
OH, YEAH, SURE, YOU JUST
LET ME KNOW WHERE IT IS, AND
I'LL TRY AND STOP BY, YEAH.

628
00:26:46,580 --> 00:26:47,580
<i>Man: OKAY, NOW CAREFUL.</i>

629
00:26:47,590 --> 00:26:48,590
[ GRUNTS ]

630
00:26:48,590 --> 00:26:50,090
SHHHH!
YEAH! GET THAT FIRE.

631
00:26:50,090 --> 00:26:52,090
<i>ESTHER HAD ONE
LIVING RELATIVE.</i>

632
00:26:52,090 --> 00:26:55,600
THEY'RE FROM OUT OF TOWN, SO
WE'LL BE DOING IT AT MY PL--
WELL, MY IN-LAWS' PLACE.

633
00:26:56,090 --> 00:26:57,090
OH, YEAH.

634
00:26:57,090 --> 00:26:58,590
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO LIVE
WITH YOUR IN-LAWS?

635
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:00,600
Danny: DAD! CHECK ME OUT!

636
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:02,100
THERE'S TROUBLE.

637
00:27:02,100 --> 00:27:03,600
YEAH, GOOD JOB.
OVER THERE, OVER THERE!

638
00:27:04,100 --> 00:27:05,610
WHAT HAVE YOU DONE NOW?
[ LAUGHS ]

639
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:07,100
UH-OH.

640
00:27:07,100 --> 00:27:09,600
AH, ALL KIDS LOVE
FIRE TRUCKS, HUH?
YEAH.

641
00:27:09,610 --> 00:27:13,110
THEY CERTAINLY UNDERSTAND
THAT LIFE IS FOR LIVING, HUH?

642
00:27:13,110 --> 00:27:14,610
HMM.
YOU HAVE CHILDREN?

643
00:27:15,110 --> 00:27:16,110
OH, YEAH. I GOT EIGHT.

644
00:27:16,110 --> 00:27:17,110
EIGHT?!
YEAH.

645
00:27:17,110 --> 00:27:18,610
WOW, YOU'RE A BLESSED MAN.

646
00:27:18,620 --> 00:27:21,620
WELL, I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE "CURSED" IS A BETTER WORD.

647
00:27:21,620 --> 00:27:23,120
[ LAUGHS ]

648
00:27:23,120 --> 00:27:26,630
BY ANY CHANCE, A, UH, YOUNG,
HANDSOME REDHEAD NAMED PETE

649
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:29,120
WOULDN'T BE IN THE O'MALLEY CLAN
OF YOURS, WOULD HE?

650
00:27:29,630 --> 00:27:32,130
LISTEN, YOU SHOULD KNOW
YOUR BRAVERY'S BEEN PASSED ON.

651
00:27:32,130 --> 00:27:35,140
HE MAY BE ONE OF
THE MORE EARNEST YOUNG MEN
I'VE EVER MET.

652
00:27:35,130 --> 00:27:36,630
LISTEN,
I WANT TO TELL YOU,

653
00:27:36,630 --> 00:27:39,630
I JUST FOUND OUT HE'S BEING
A NUISANCE OVER THERE
AT YOUR TEMPLE,

654
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:41,640
AND I'VE TALKED TO HIM,
REPRIMANDED HIM,

655
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:44,640
AND BELIEVE ME, HE'S NOT GONNA
BE BOTHERING YOU ANYMORE.

656
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:46,150
I RESPECT YOUR WISHES.

657
00:27:46,140 --> 00:27:47,640
YOU SHOULD KNOW, THOUGH,

658
00:27:47,650 --> 00:27:50,150
THAT HE'S WELCOME
AT MY TEMPLE ANYTIME.

659
00:27:50,150 --> 00:27:51,650
YEAH.

660
00:27:51,650 --> 00:27:53,650
NICE AND SHORT --
THE HAIR.

661
00:27:53,650 --> 00:27:56,660
I GOTTA BATTLE WITH MY KIDS
TO KEEP THEIR HAIR SHORT.

662
00:27:56,650 --> 00:27:59,150
THAT'S THE WAY A KID'S HAIR
SHOULD BE.

663
00:27:59,160 --> 00:28:02,660
YEAH, HE'S, UH, HE'S ACTUALLY
TRYING TO GROW HIS OUT.

664
00:28:02,660 --> 00:28:06,170
UH, HE UNDERWENT CHEMOTHERAPY
ABOUT SIX MONTHS AGO --

665
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:07,660
<i>UH, LEUKEMIA.</i>

666
00:28:07,670 --> 00:28:08,670
LEUKEMIA?

667
00:28:08,670 --> 00:28:09,670
<i>YEAH.</i>

668
00:28:09,670 --> 00:28:11,170
HE'S IN REMISSION.

669
00:28:11,170 --> 00:28:13,170
WE'RE ALL VERY HOPEFUL.

670
00:28:13,170 --> 00:28:14,670
GOD HAS A PLAN...

671
00:28:14,670 --> 00:28:18,180
ALBEIT A MYSTERIOUS ONE,
FOR MY FAMILY.

672
00:28:18,180 --> 00:28:21,180
SO, LOOK, WHEN YOU GET
THE TIME,

673
00:28:21,180 --> 00:28:24,180
UH, COME ON BY AND --
<i>AND BRING PETE.</i>

674
00:28:24,180 --> 00:28:27,190
<i>SURE.
I THINK IT WOULD DO
EVERYBODY'S SPIRIT'S GOOD</i>

675
00:28:27,180 --> 00:28:29,680
TO SEE A YOUNG MAN
SO FULL OF LIFE
THE WAY YOUR SON IS.

676
00:28:30,190 --> 00:28:33,190
YEAH, YEAH, HE'S FULL OF
SOMETHING. [ CHUCKLES ]

677
00:28:33,190 --> 00:28:35,700
<i>Children on TV:
LEFT FOOT, RIGHT FOOT,
GO, GO, GO!</i>

678
00:28:35,690 --> 00:28:37,690
<i>LEFT FOOT, RIGHT FOOT...</i>

679
00:28:37,700 --> 00:28:39,700
HEY, GETTING THE MAIL'S
MY JOB!

680
00:28:39,700 --> 00:28:41,700
IT'S YOUR JOB?

681
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:44,200
YOU WANT THE MAIL?

682
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:46,210
<i>[ LAUGHTER ]</i>

683
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:47,700
YOU WANT THE MAIL?

684
00:28:48,210 --> 00:28:50,710
YOU WANT THE MAIL,
HUH? HUH?

685
00:28:50,710 --> 00:28:53,710
WHAT ARE YOU
LOOKING FOR?

686
00:28:53,710 --> 00:28:57,220
BILLS...BILL...

687
00:28:57,210 --> 00:28:58,210
BILLS.

688
00:28:58,720 --> 00:28:59,720
NOTHING BUT BILLS.

689
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:02,220
<i>...SPECIAL GUEST
IN THE CLUBHOUSE TODAY.</i>

690
00:29:02,220 --> 00:29:05,230
<i>HE CAME ALL THE WAY
FROM THE LINCOLN PARK ZOO!</i>

691
00:29:05,220 --> 00:29:06,720
COME ON.

692
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:09,720
<i>LET'S SAY A BIG HELLO
TO ZOOKEEPER ROB!</i>

693
00:29:09,730 --> 00:29:12,730
HEY, I DIDN'T SAY YOU COULD GO.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

694
00:29:12,730 --> 00:29:14,230
<i>Margaret:
PETER, SEAMUS -- NOW!</i>

695
00:29:14,730 --> 00:29:16,240
LET'S GO!

696
00:29:16,230 --> 00:29:18,230
GET IN HERE!

697
00:29:18,240 --> 00:29:21,740
OH, HONEY, PLEASE,
CAN I BE THE YELLER TODAY?

698
00:29:21,740 --> 00:29:23,240
OKAY, IS THAT EVERYTHING?
YES.

699
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:25,250
NOTHING UNDER YOUR BEDS?
<i>COME ON.
NOPE.</i>

700
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:26,740
NOTHING IN THE CLOSET?

701
00:29:26,740 --> 00:29:28,740
<i>MNH-MNH. NOPE.
YOU DIDN'T HIDE ANYTHING
IN YOUR SISTER'S ROOM?</i>

702
00:29:29,250 --> 00:29:30,250
UNH-UNH.
IN THE BATHTUB?

703
00:29:30,250 --> 00:29:32,250
MOM, IT'S ALL IN THERE.
NOTHING BEHIND THE DOORS?

704
00:29:32,250 --> 00:29:34,250
YOU DON'T HAVE TWO PAIRS OF
PANTS ON RIGHT NOW, DO YOU?

705
00:29:34,750 --> 00:29:36,760
<i>'CAUSE I'M WASHING
EVERYTHING.
NO, IT'S ALL IN THERE.</i>

706
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:38,750
ANYTHING IN THE SINK?
WHAT TIME --

707
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:41,260
NOTHING UNDER THE BEDS...
WHAT TIME DOES
THE BOYS' GAME START?

708
00:29:41,260 --> 00:29:43,260
Seamus: 6:00, BUT IT'S
<i>A DOUBLE-HEADER.
MM-HMM.</i>

709
00:29:43,260 --> 00:29:46,770
UNCLE ROGER'S COMING.
SO IS BILLY AND ROBERT JR.

710
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:49,260
YEAH...

711
00:29:49,270 --> 00:29:51,270
DID YOU FINISH YOUR CHORES?

712
00:29:51,270 --> 00:29:52,770
YEAH.

713
00:29:52,770 --> 00:29:54,770
<i>ALL RIGHT.</i>

714
00:29:54,770 --> 00:29:58,280
HEY, YOU AND I ARE INVITED
TO A "CHIVAS" AT THE RABBI'S.

715
00:29:58,280 --> 00:29:59,780
CHIVAS?

716
00:29:59,780 --> 00:30:01,280
<i>YEAH, IT'S KIND OF
LIKE A WAKE.</i>

717
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:03,780
<i>I TOLD THEM
WE'D TRY AND STOP BY.</i>

718
00:30:03,780 --> 00:30:05,290
WELL, HOW'S HE DOING?

719
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:07,280
WELL, I DON'T THINK
HE'S TOO HAPPY.

720
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:10,280
THAT LADY THAT DIED WAS HIS
SECRETARY FOR, LIKE, 40 YEARS
OR SOMETHING.

721
00:30:10,290 --> 00:30:11,790
I DON'T THINK HE'S TOO HAPPY
RIGHT NOW.

722
00:30:11,790 --> 00:30:14,290
HONEY, HE LOST SOMEBODY
HE LOVES VERY, VERY MUCH,

723
00:30:14,290 --> 00:30:16,300
AND I'M SURE HE'LL BE SAD
<i>FOR A WHILE.</i>

724
00:30:16,290 --> 00:30:18,790
HIS LITTLE BOY WAS SAVED,
AND THAT'S THE GOOD SIDE,
<i>RIGHT?</i>

725
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:19,800
<i>YEAH.</i>

726
00:30:20,300 --> 00:30:22,300
SO, ANYWAY, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE, HUH?

727
00:30:22,300 --> 00:30:24,300
TELL RABBI JACOBSEN
I'M SORRY.

728
00:30:24,300 --> 00:30:26,310
<i>CAN I HEAR
A "THANK YOU, DAD"?</i>

729
00:30:26,300 --> 00:30:27,800
<i>THANK YOU, DAD!
THERE YOU GO.</i>

730
00:30:27,810 --> 00:30:29,810
SO WE'LL GO, AND THEN
WE'LL CATCH THE SECOND GAME,
ALL RIGHT?

731
00:30:29,810 --> 00:30:32,810
OKAY.
<i>YOU KNOW WHAT -- THE RABBI'S
SON IS YOUR AGE, HONEY.</i>

732
00:30:32,810 --> 00:30:35,820
SO WHEN YOU GO THERE,
YOU SAY TO HIM HOW SORRY
YOU ARE, ALL RIGHT?

733
00:30:35,810 --> 00:30:37,310
OKAY, I WILL, MOM.

734
00:30:37,310 --> 00:30:38,310
<i>ALL RIGHT.</i>

735
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:40,820
HE'S PROBABLY JEWISH,
RIGHT?

736
00:30:40,820 --> 00:30:44,320
I WOULD THINK THERE'S
A HIGH LIKELIHOOD OF THAT.

737
00:30:44,320 --> 00:30:47,330
<i>I NEED YOU TO WASH UP, <i>HONEY.
HERE, YOU CAN WEAR
THIS AND THIS.</i>

738
00:30:47,830 --> 00:30:50,330
HERE, PUT THOSE ON.
TUCK THE SHIRT IN,
WASH YOUR FACE.

739
00:30:50,330 --> 00:30:51,830
OKAY, MOM, I WILL.
<i>SOAP AND WATER.</i>

740
00:30:52,330 --> 00:30:53,330
I WILL, MOM.
<i>OKAY.</i>

741
00:30:53,330 --> 00:30:55,840
YOU DO THE SAME THING.
GO WASH YOUR FACE.

742
00:30:55,830 --> 00:30:58,330
I LOVE IT WHEN YOU TALK TO ME
LIKE I'M 9.

743
00:30:58,340 --> 00:31:00,840
WELL, WHO ELSE DO I TALK TO
ALL DAY BUT --

744
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:01,840
COME HERE. HEY.

745
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:03,340
WHAT?

746
00:31:03,340 --> 00:31:05,850
YOU WANT TO MAKE OUT?

747
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:06,840
WITH YOU?

748
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:08,340
[ CHUCKLES ]

749
00:31:10,710 --> 00:31:12,840
I DON'T WANT TO GO
TO THE RABBI'S

750
00:31:12,850 --> 00:31:14,350
OR WHEREVER THIS THING IS.

751
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:17,360
HONEY, YOU SAID YOU WOULD,
AND YOU'RE GONNA GO.

752
00:31:17,350 --> 00:31:19,850
YEAH, SO, I CAN'T SAY NO TO HIM
RIGHT THERE.

753
00:31:20,360 --> 00:31:22,360
I MEAN, JEEZ...

754
00:31:22,860 --> 00:31:27,370
THE GUY LOSES THE LADY THAT HE'S
KNOWN ALL OF HIS LIFE.

755
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:29,360
HIS HOUSE IS IN ASHES.

756
00:31:29,370 --> 00:31:32,370
BESIDES THAT,
HIS KID'S GOT LEUKEMIA.

757
00:31:32,870 --> 00:31:34,370
WHAT?

758
00:31:34,370 --> 00:31:35,880
YEAH.

759
00:31:35,870 --> 00:31:39,370
I MEAN, HOW AM I GONNA SAY NO
TO THAT?

760
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,380
WHY, YOU DON'T.

761
00:31:41,380 --> 00:31:43,380
IT'S THAT OLD
ELECTRICAL WIRING.

762
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:45,390
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

763
00:31:48,390 --> 00:31:49,390
HEY, MOM.

764
00:31:49,390 --> 00:31:50,890
OH, HI, HONEY.

765
00:31:50,890 --> 00:31:51,890
HOW YOU DOING?

766
00:31:52,390 --> 00:31:54,390
YOUR DINNER'S WARM.
IT'S IN THE OVEN.

767
00:31:54,890 --> 00:31:57,400
USE THAT TOWEL THERE.
DON'T BURN YOUR HAND.

768
00:31:57,390 --> 00:31:59,890
YOU WANT SOMETHING TO DRINK
WITH THAT?

769
00:31:59,900 --> 00:32:01,400
UH, NO. I'M ALL RIGHT.

770
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,400
WATER?

771
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:03,400
<i>NO.</i>

772
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:04,900
HEY, LIFESAVER.

773
00:32:04,900 --> 00:32:08,410
YOUR MA SAYS YOU GOT
SOMETHING TO TELL ME.

774
00:32:10,410 --> 00:32:12,410
UH...

775
00:32:12,410 --> 00:32:15,420
I THINK I'M GONNA TAKE A LOOK
AT THAT JOB

776
00:32:15,410 --> 00:32:17,410
AT THE CITY PLANNER'S
OFFICE.

777
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:21,420
THAT'S A GOOD JOB.

778
00:32:21,420 --> 00:32:22,920
IT'S GOT NICE BENEFITS.

779
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:26,930
I'LL TALK TO ALDERMAN McMANUS
<i>ABOUT IT.</i>

780
00:32:27,420 --> 00:32:27,920
<i>WHAT?</i>

781
00:32:28,430 --> 00:32:29,430
WHAT'S THAT LOOK?

782
00:32:29,430 --> 00:32:30,430
DON'T EVEN GO IN THERE

783
00:32:30,430 --> 00:32:32,930
IF YOU'RE GONNA GO IN THERE
WITH THAT ATTITUDE, PAL.

784
00:32:32,930 --> 00:32:34,430
<i>ALL RIGHT?</i>

785
00:32:34,430 --> 00:32:36,440
<i>THE ALDERMAN'S
DOING US A FAVOR, OKAY?</i>

786
00:32:36,430 --> 00:32:38,930
SO DON'T GO IN THERE ACTING
<i>LIKE A PUNK.</i>

787
00:32:38,940 --> 00:32:41,440
A LOT OF KIDS YOUR AGE
DON'T HAVE A CHANCE LIKE THIS.

788
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:43,940
<i>NO, ACTUALLY, A LOT OF KIDS
MY AGE GO TO COLLEGE.</i>

789
00:32:43,940 --> 00:32:46,950
AND THEY'RE FOUR YEARS BEHIND
EVERYONE ELSE IN THE WORKFORCE,

790
00:32:46,940 --> 00:32:48,440
AND WHAT HAVE THEY LEARNED?

791
00:32:48,450 --> 00:32:50,450
HOW TO SMOKE POT
AND HOW TO SLEEP ALL DAY.

792
00:32:50,950 --> 00:32:54,450
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
THAT THE GOOD JOBS

793
00:32:54,450 --> 00:32:58,460
REQUIRE, <i>REQUIRE
A COLLEGE DEGREE TODAY?</i>

794
00:32:58,460 --> 00:33:01,960
A CITY JOB <i>IS A GOOD JOB,
AND ALL IT REQUIRES</i>

795
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:04,960
IS A LITTLE HARD WORK
AND THE RIGHT ATTITUDE.

796
00:33:05,460 --> 00:33:08,460
THAT'S MY ONLY CHOICE, THEN --
THE IRISH WAY. THAT'S IT? HUH?

797
00:33:08,470 --> 00:33:11,970
I GOTTA GET A CITY JOB, WORK
MY ASS OFF, HAVE 40 KIDS, HUH?

798
00:33:11,970 --> 00:33:13,970
SO I CAN RETIRE
ON A CRAP PENSION

799
00:33:13,970 --> 00:33:17,480
AND LIVE IN THE SAME HOUSE
I'VE LIVED IN MY WHOLE LIFE?!

800
00:33:17,470 --> 00:33:18,970
HEY, YOU LOWER YOUR VOICE.

801
00:33:18,980 --> 00:33:21,980
THAT'S OUR LIFE YOU'RE
TALKING ABOUT, PAL.

802
00:33:21,980 --> 00:33:24,480
WHAT, YOU WANT TO BE
A HOTSHOT DOCTOR,

803
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:27,490
HAVE 1.2 KIDS AND A BIG HOUSE
IN THE SUBURBS

804
00:33:27,480 --> 00:33:29,480
WITH ENOUGH LOVE TO FILL
A CLOSET

805
00:33:29,490 --> 00:33:31,990
SO THAT YOU CAN FINALLY RETIRE
TO FLORIDA

806
00:33:31,990 --> 00:33:33,490
AND DIE LIKE A RAISIN?

807
00:33:33,490 --> 00:33:34,490
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

808
00:33:34,490 --> 00:33:36,500
MAYBE I DO.
WHY CAN'T I JUST DO THAT?!

809
00:33:36,490 --> 00:33:38,490
THEN GO AHEAD!
BE LIKE THE JEWS!

810
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:41,000
HAVE NO MORE THAN TWO KIDS

811
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:44,500
'CAUSE IT'S NOT ECONOMICAL
<i>TO HAVE MORE!</i>

812
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:47,010
RAISE YOUR KIDS TO BASE
THEIR LIFE

813
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,500
ON THE SIZE OF THEIR WALLET!

814
00:33:48,510 --> 00:33:50,510
YEAH, THAT'S --
THAT'S RIGHT, POP. YEAH.

815
00:33:50,510 --> 00:33:53,010
WHY IN THE WORLD SHOULD
I RAISE MY KIDS

816
00:33:53,010 --> 00:33:55,010
TO BASE THEIR WORTH ON THE SIZE
OF THEIR WALLET?

817
00:33:55,510 --> 00:33:57,010
THAT'S CRAZY!

818
00:33:57,010 --> 00:33:59,510
YOU SHOULD BASE IT TO SEE HOW
MUCH BOOZE THEY CAN DRINK

819
00:34:00,020 --> 00:34:01,520
WITHOUT PUKING, HUH?
IS THAT IT?

820
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:04,020
JOE! JOE!
HUH?! HUH?!

821
00:34:04,020 --> 00:34:07,530
YOU UNGRATEFUL,
SMART-MOUTH PUNK.

822
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:11,520
YOU GOT ALL THE ANSWERS AT 18,
DON'T YOU?

823
00:34:11,530 --> 00:34:12,530
HUH?

824
00:34:12,530 --> 00:34:15,540
NO...I DON'T.

825
00:34:15,530 --> 00:34:19,030
MAYBE IF I GO WORK AT THE CITY
PLANNER'S OFFICE,

826
00:34:19,040 --> 00:34:22,540
I'LL GET THEM BY THE TIME
I TURN 40, LIKE YOU, HUH?

827
00:34:22,540 --> 00:34:24,040
LET IT GO, JOE.

828
00:34:24,040 --> 00:34:26,550
YOU BETTER GET OUT OF HERE
RIGHT NOW.

829
00:34:26,540 --> 00:34:28,540
I'M LEAVING.

830
00:34:31,550 --> 00:34:33,550
CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT KID?

831
00:34:33,550 --> 00:34:36,060
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

832
00:34:36,050 --> 00:34:39,550
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

833
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:41,560
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

834
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:43,060
GIVE THESE TO THAT MAN.

835
00:34:43,060 --> 00:34:46,070
HI. I'M JEFFREY JACOBSEN,
RABBI KENNY'S BROTHER.

836
00:34:46,060 --> 00:34:48,060
JOE O'MALLEY.
MY SON PETE.

837
00:34:48,070 --> 00:34:49,070
THIS IS FOR YOU.

838
00:34:49,070 --> 00:34:50,070
OH, IT'S, UH --

839
00:34:50,570 --> 00:34:52,570
I'LL GO PUT THESE
IN THE KITCHEN.

840
00:34:52,570 --> 00:34:54,570
THANKS.
ESTHER LOVED FLOWERS.

841
00:34:54,570 --> 00:34:55,580
OKAY, GOOD.

842
00:34:55,570 --> 00:34:56,570
HEY.

843
00:34:56,570 --> 00:34:58,070
HEY. HOW YOU DOING?

844
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,080
GOOD.
GOOD.

845
00:34:59,080 --> 00:35:02,080
HEY, WANT TO CHECK OUT THE ROOM
THAT I'M STAYING IN?

846
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:04,580
SURE. CAN I?
SURE. YEAH. GO AHEAD.

847
00:35:04,580 --> 00:35:06,590
CAN I GET YOU SOMETHING
TO DRINK?

848
00:35:06,580 --> 00:35:08,580
UH, YEAH. I'LL JUST HAVE
A SCOTCH IF YOU GOT IT.

849
00:35:09,090 --> 00:35:11,590
UH, I'LL HAVE TO CHECK TO SEE IF
I HAVE ANY SCOTCH. IF NOT...

850
00:35:11,590 --> 00:35:13,090
OH, A BEER WOULD BE FINE.

851
00:35:13,090 --> 00:35:14,590
OKAY, I'LL HAVE TO, UH,

852
00:35:14,590 --> 00:35:16,600
I'LL HAVE TO CHECK TO SEE
IF I HAVE ANY BEER.

853
00:35:16,590 --> 00:35:17,590
IF NOT, UM...

854
00:35:17,590 --> 00:35:20,090
UH, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M FINE.

855
00:35:20,100 --> 00:35:22,600
YOU SURE?
NO, I'M ABSOLUTELY FINE.

856
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:23,600
THANK YOU.

857
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:26,110
OH, MRS. JACOBSEN.
HI. HOW ARE YOU?

858
00:35:26,100 --> 00:35:27,100
THANKS FOR BEING HERE.

859
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:29,600
OH, I'M SORRY ABOUT...
WHAT HAPPENED.

860
00:35:30,110 --> 00:35:31,110
YOUR SON LOOKS GOOD.

861
00:35:31,110 --> 00:35:32,610
YEAH, HE DOES, DOESN'T HE?

862
00:35:33,110 --> 00:35:35,620
YEAH, HE LOOKS GOOD.
RABBI, HOW ARE YOU?

863
00:35:35,610 --> 00:35:37,610
GOOD, GOOD.
THANKS FOR COMING.

864
00:35:37,610 --> 00:35:39,110
MY PLEASURE TO BE HERE.

865
00:35:39,120 --> 00:35:40,120
APPRECIATE IT.

866
00:35:40,120 --> 00:35:41,120
WELL, YEAH.

867
00:35:41,120 --> 00:35:42,620
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

868
00:35:42,620 --> 00:35:44,620
CAN WE GET YOU ANYTHING?

869
00:35:44,620 --> 00:35:47,130
UH, WATER WOULD BE FINE...

870
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:48,620
IF YOU GOT WATER.

871
00:35:50,630 --> 00:35:52,630
DO YOU PLAY ON A TEAM?

872
00:35:52,630 --> 00:35:54,630
NO. I COULDN'T THIS YEAR.

873
00:35:54,630 --> 00:35:56,140
I GOT LEUKEMIA.

874
00:35:56,130 --> 00:35:57,630
<i>IT'S CANCER.</i>

875
00:35:57,630 --> 00:36:01,630
I TOOK THIS MEDICINE
THAT MADE ME LOSE MY HAIR,

876
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:04,140
BUT IT'S GROWING BACK.

877
00:36:04,140 --> 00:36:06,150
DID IT HURT?

878
00:36:06,140 --> 00:36:08,640
NO. JUST FELL OUT.

879
00:36:08,650 --> 00:36:10,150
I DON'T REALLY FEEL IT,

880
00:36:10,150 --> 00:36:12,650
BUT IT'S BEEN IN REMISSION
FOR SIX MONTHS.

881
00:36:12,650 --> 00:36:14,150
REMISSION?

882
00:36:14,150 --> 00:36:17,660
MEANS
IT'S STILL KIND OF THERE,

883
00:36:17,650 --> 00:36:20,150
BUT IT'S NOT REALLY
BOTHERING ME.

884
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:22,660
I SWEAR, MY HAIR WASN'T THIS
LIGHT BEFORE.

885
00:36:27,160 --> 00:36:29,160
WAS THE FIRE SCARY?

886
00:36:29,170 --> 00:36:31,170
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

887
00:36:31,170 --> 00:36:33,670
I WAS UPSTAIRS PLAYING
IN MY ROOM,

888
00:36:33,670 --> 00:36:35,680
AND THEN I SAW A LOT
OF SMOKE.

889
00:36:36,170 --> 00:36:38,670
THEN YOUR DAD CAME IN
AND SAVED MY LIFE.

890
00:36:39,180 --> 00:36:43,180
BUT IT'S <i>NOTHING LIKE THE FIRE
DRILLS WE DO IN SCHOOL.</i>

891
00:36:43,180 --> 00:36:46,690
SPEAKING OF SCHOOL,
WHAT GRADE ARE YOU IN?

892
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:50,180
I'M GOING INTO SECOND OVER
AT BRIARWOOD.

893
00:36:50,190 --> 00:36:54,190
I'M GOING INTO THIRD
OVER AT HOLY CROSS.

894
00:36:54,190 --> 00:36:57,200
WHAT'S IT LIKE TO BE JEWISH?

895
00:36:57,190 --> 00:36:58,690
I DON'T KNOW.

896
00:36:58,700 --> 00:36:59,700
GOOD.

897
00:36:59,700 --> 00:37:01,700
I'M CATHOLIC.

898
00:37:01,700 --> 00:37:03,700
<i>WHAT'S THAT LIKE?</i>

899
00:37:03,700 --> 00:37:05,200
NOISIER.

900
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:07,710
THINGS ARE USUALLY NOISIER
AROUND HERE,

901
00:37:07,700 --> 00:37:10,200
BUT IT'S BEEN QUIETER BECAUSE
OF THE <i>SHIVA.</i>

902
00:37:10,210 --> 00:37:13,210
YOU SHOULD'VE BEEN
AT MY UNCLE JIM'S FUNERAL.

903
00:37:13,210 --> 00:37:16,220
YOU WOULD'VE THOUGHT
IT WAS A BIRTHDAY PARTY.

904
00:37:16,210 --> 00:37:19,710
MY MOM SAID THAT EVERYONE'S SAD
BECAUSE THE PERSON DIED,

905
00:37:19,720 --> 00:37:23,220
BUT THEN AGAIN, THEY'RE HAPPY
BECAUSE HE GETS TO GO TO HEAVEN.

906
00:37:23,220 --> 00:37:25,730
JEWISH PEOPLE CAN'T GO
TO HEAVEN.

907
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:26,720
WHY NOT?

908
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:28,220
'CAUSE THEY'RE JEWISH.

909
00:37:28,230 --> 00:37:31,730
GOD DOESN'T LET JEWISH PEOPLE
<i>INTO HEAVEN.</i>

910
00:37:31,730 --> 00:37:35,230
BUT IF YOU'RE INTERESTED,
MAYBE I COULD HELP
YOU GET TO HEAVEN.

911
00:37:35,230 --> 00:37:36,240
YEAH?

912
00:37:36,230 --> 00:37:37,730
<i>YEP.</i>

913
00:37:37,730 --> 00:37:40,230
<i>ALL I HAVE TO DO
IS CONVERT YOU.</i>

914
00:37:40,240 --> 00:37:41,240
HOW DO YOU DO THAT?

915
00:37:41,240 --> 00:37:42,740
I DON'T KNOW.

916
00:37:42,740 --> 00:37:46,750
I'VE NEVER ACTUALLY CONVERTED
ANYONE BEFORE.

917
00:37:46,740 --> 00:37:49,240
SO WHAT CAN I DO IN HEAVEN?

918
00:37:49,250 --> 00:37:51,250
ANYTHING YOU WANT.

919
00:37:51,250 --> 00:37:53,750
THEY CALL IT PARADISE.

920
00:37:53,750 --> 00:37:55,250
SOUNDS GOOD.

921
00:37:55,250 --> 00:37:57,260
SO WHEN CAN WE START?

922
00:37:57,250 --> 00:38:00,750
MEET ME AT YOUR SYNAGOGUE
TOMORROW.

923
00:38:01,260 --> 00:38:02,260
ALL RIGHT.

924
00:38:02,260 --> 00:38:03,760
WE GOT A RAIN DELAY?

925
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:05,770
<i>Man: YEAH, 15 MINUTES, JOE.</i>

926
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:09,260
OH, YEAH? ALL RIGHT.
WELL, WE'LL STAY HERE.

927
00:38:09,770 --> 00:38:12,270
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

928
00:38:12,770 --> 00:38:15,270
SO, DANNY'S A GOOD KID, HUH?

929
00:38:15,270 --> 00:38:18,280
YEAH. HIS HAIR'S SHORT BECAUSE
OF THE MEDICINE,

930
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,780
BUT IT'S GROWING BACK.

931
00:38:19,780 --> 00:38:22,280
YOU DIDN'T TRY
SAYING ANYTHING TO HIM

932
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:25,280
ABOUT WHAT WE, UH,
TALKED ABOUT, DID YOU?

933
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:28,290
BUT, DAD, DANNY WANTS
TO DO IT, ALSO.

934
00:38:30,290 --> 00:38:31,790
WHAT DID I SAY?

935
00:38:31,790 --> 00:38:33,790
HIS FAMILY IS JEWISH.

936
00:38:33,790 --> 00:38:35,290
HE'S JEWISH.

937
00:38:35,290 --> 00:38:37,300
THEY DON'T WANT TO BE
CHRISTIAN.

938
00:38:37,290 --> 00:38:38,290
BUT IT'S A QUEST.

939
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:40,800
YOUR QUEST IS CALLED OFF,
MY FRIEND.

940
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:42,300
BUT I PROMISED DANNY.

941
00:38:42,300 --> 00:38:44,800
WE'RE MEETING
AT THE SYNAGOGUE --

942
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:45,810
NO, YOU'RE NOT!

943
00:38:48,310 --> 00:38:50,310
YOU DON'T GO TRYING TO CONVERT
JEWISH KIDS

944
00:38:50,310 --> 00:38:52,810
THE SAME WAY THEY DON'T COME
OVER HERE TRYING TO CONVERT US!

945
00:38:52,810 --> 00:38:54,310
BUT HE WANTS TO DO IT.

946
00:38:54,310 --> 00:38:57,820
I SAID NO, AND I DON'T WANT TO
HEAR ANOTHER WORD FROM YOU!

947
00:38:57,810 --> 00:38:59,810
YOU DO NOT GO TO THAT TEMPLE
<i>ANYMORE.</i>

948
00:38:59,820 --> 00:39:01,820
YOU DO NOT BOTHER DANNY
OR HIS FAMILY ANYMORE.

949
00:39:02,320 --> 00:39:03,320
AND, SO HELP ME, GOD,

950
00:39:03,320 --> 00:39:05,320
IF I FIND OUT YOU'VE BEEN GOING
OVER THERE,

951
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:07,330
YOU'RE GONNA GET THE SPANKING
OF A LIFETIME,

952
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:09,320
AND YOU'RE GONNA BE GROUNDED
UNTIL YOU'RE 16,

953
00:39:09,830 --> 00:39:12,330
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?!

954
00:39:12,330 --> 00:39:13,700
YES, SIR.

955
00:39:13,700 --> 00:39:16,340
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

956
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:25,850
MR. O'MALLEY.

957
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:27,340
YOU LOST?

958
00:39:27,340 --> 00:39:28,340
HEY, FATHER.

959
00:39:28,850 --> 00:39:30,350
NO, I'M NOT LOST.

960
00:39:30,350 --> 00:39:34,350
<i>I JUST HAVE A LOT MORE
QUESTIONS THAN ANSWERS.</i>

961
00:39:34,350 --> 00:39:35,860
AH.

962
00:39:40,360 --> 00:39:41,860
[ SIGHS ]

963
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:47,360
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

964
00:39:47,860 --> 00:39:49,860
I'M JUST GONNA CHECK OUT WHAT
THIS PLACE LOOKS LIKE

965
00:39:50,370 --> 00:39:51,370
FROM YOUR SEAT.

966
00:39:51,370 --> 00:39:53,370
THAT'S MY CHAIR.
DON'T BREAK IT.

967
00:39:55,870 --> 00:39:57,870
DO YOU GET THE COLLECTION
MONEY?

968
00:39:57,870 --> 00:39:58,870
[ Chuckles ] NO.

969
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:01,380
WHY,
DID SOMEONE TELL YOU I DID?

970
00:40:01,380 --> 00:40:04,380
NO. BUT THEN,
HOW DO YOU GET PAID?

971
00:40:04,380 --> 00:40:07,890
[ SIGHS ] DON'T YOU NEED TO GET
HOME, MR. O'MALLEY?

972
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:10,880
YOUR JOB IS TO HELP PEOPLE
GET TO HEAVEN, RIGHT?

973
00:40:10,890 --> 00:40:12,890
YES.

974
00:40:12,890 --> 00:40:16,400
BUT HAVE YOU EVER ACTUALLY SEEN
<i>SOMEONE IN HEAVEN?</i>

975
00:40:16,390 --> 00:40:17,890
NO.

976
00:40:17,890 --> 00:40:20,390
WELL, THEN, HOW DO YOU KNOW
IF THEY MADE IT TO HEAVEN?

977
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:26,410
FAITH.

978
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:28,900
FAITH?

979
00:40:28,910 --> 00:40:29,910
YEP.

980
00:40:29,910 --> 00:40:32,910
BELIEVING IN SOMETHING
COMPLETELY

981
00:40:32,910 --> 00:40:36,420
WITHOUT ACTUALLY HAVING
ANY PROOF OF IT.

982
00:40:36,910 --> 00:40:37,910
<i>FAITH.</i>

983
00:40:37,910 --> 00:40:40,910
<i>I-I DON'T HAVE ANY PROOF
OF HEAVEN,</i>

984
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:42,920
BUT I HAVE FAITH IT EXISTS.

985
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:45,420
WHAT'S THE BEST WAY
TO GET TO HEAVEN?

986
00:40:45,420 --> 00:40:47,430
BELIEVING IN JESUS.

987
00:40:47,420 --> 00:40:51,920
LIVING THE WAY HE TAUGHT US
TO LIVE.

988
00:40:51,930 --> 00:40:54,930
WELL, HOW DO WE KNOW
IF WE'RE DOING THAT?

989
00:40:54,930 --> 00:40:57,440
IS THERE, LIKE,
SOME KIND OF TEST?

990
00:40:57,430 --> 00:40:59,430
WELL, YOUR LIFE IS THE TEST.

991
00:40:59,940 --> 00:41:02,440
SO, THEN, YOU HAVE TO DIE
TO FIND OUT HOW YOU DID
ON THE TEST.

992
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:05,950
I GUESS SO.

993
00:41:05,940 --> 00:41:08,940
DON'T YOU JUST ONCE
WANT TO KNOW

994
00:41:08,950 --> 00:41:12,950
IF ONE OF THE PEOPLE YOU PRAY
FOR MADE IT TO HEAVEN?

995
00:41:12,950 --> 00:41:14,950
[ SIGHS ]

996
00:41:14,950 --> 00:41:16,960
IN DUE TIME.

997
00:41:28,970 --> 00:41:31,970
WHAT'S THE PURPOSE
OF COMMUNION?

998
00:41:31,970 --> 00:41:34,470
TO MAKE A PART OF JESUS
A PART OF US.

999
00:41:34,470 --> 00:41:38,480
<i>WELL, THEN, WHY DO I HAVE TO
WAIT TILL THIRD GRADE?</i>

1000
00:41:38,480 --> 00:41:40,480
I MEAN,
WOULDN'T IT HELP ME NOW?

1001
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:42,980
THE CHURCH BELIEVES
<i>THAT CATHOLICS</i>

1002
00:41:42,980 --> 00:41:45,480
SHOULD FULFILL
A FEW REQUIREMENTS

1003
00:41:45,980 --> 00:41:49,480
BEFORE THEY EARN THE SACRAMENT
OF COMMUNION.

1004
00:41:49,490 --> 00:41:51,490
<i>LIKE PASSING A FEW TESTS.</i>

1005
00:41:51,490 --> 00:41:52,990
YES.

1006
00:41:52,990 --> 00:41:58,500
SO IF I PASS ALL THE TESTS,
I CAN GET COMMUNION?

1007
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:01,000
YES.

1008
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,000
THANKS, FATHER.

1009
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:05,000
YOU CLEARED UP
QUITE A FEW THINGS FOR ME.

1010
00:42:08,240 --> 00:42:10,740
[ HORN HONKING, BIRDS CHIRPING ]

1011
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:15,740
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

1012
00:42:15,750 --> 00:42:18,250
OUR QUEST HAS TO BE DONE
IN SECRET.

1013
00:42:18,250 --> 00:42:20,250
OUR MISSION
IS NOW UNDERCOVER.

1014
00:42:20,250 --> 00:42:21,250
WHY?

1015
00:42:21,250 --> 00:42:23,760
JUST FOLLOW ME.

1016
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:31,760
SO, THIS DOESN'T ACTUALLY REALLY
LOOK LIKE IT'S UNDERCOVER,

1017
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:34,770
<i>BUT WHY ARE WE UNDERCOVER?</i>

1018
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:37,760
WELL, 'CAUSE.

1019
00:42:37,770 --> 00:42:39,770
SO, WHAT'S OUR MISSION?

1020
00:42:39,770 --> 00:42:41,270
TO GET YOU TO HEAVEN.

1021
00:42:41,770 --> 00:42:44,780
RIGHT. SO, HOW AM I GONNA GET
TO HEAVEN?

1022
00:42:44,770 --> 00:42:46,270
I DON'T KNOW.

1023
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:48,280
YOU GOTTA HAVE SOME IDEAS.

1024
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:49,280
WELL...

1025
00:42:49,780 --> 00:42:51,780
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO SET UP
SOME TESTS.

1026
00:42:52,280 --> 00:42:54,790
HAVE YOU TAKEN
ANY OF THESE TESTS?

1027
00:42:54,780 --> 00:42:58,280
NEXT YEAR, I HAVE TO COMPLETE
FIRST-COMMUNION TRAINING.

1028
00:42:58,290 --> 00:43:00,790
WHAT'S COMMUNION?

1029
00:43:00,790 --> 00:43:03,300
THIS PIECE OF BREAD
THAT'S JESUS.

1030
00:43:03,290 --> 00:43:05,290
AND YOU EAT IT?

1031
00:43:05,300 --> 00:43:06,300
<i>YEAH.</i>

1032
00:43:06,300 --> 00:43:07,300
GROSS!

1033
00:43:07,300 --> 00:43:10,300
<i>SO I SHOULD DO THE
FIRST-COMMUNION TRAINING,</i>

1034
00:43:10,300 --> 00:43:11,800
SHOULDN'T I?

1035
00:43:11,800 --> 00:43:15,310
WELL, I HAVEN'T DONE IT YET,
SO I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE.

1036
00:43:17,310 --> 00:43:18,810
BUT WE CAN MAKE UP SOME TESTS
OF OUR OWN.

1037
00:43:18,810 --> 00:43:21,810
HOW ABOUT SOMETHING LIKE
A BRUCE JENNER?

1038
00:43:21,810 --> 00:43:24,320
<i>WIN THE DECATHLON,
GO TO HEAVEN.</i>

1039
00:43:24,310 --> 00:43:26,810
YEAH, SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

1040
00:43:26,820 --> 00:43:29,320
AND THEN WE SHOULD HAVE
A GOLD-MEDAL CEREMONY.

1041
00:43:29,320 --> 00:43:30,820
GOTTA HAVE A MEDAL.

1042
00:43:30,820 --> 00:43:33,330
COMMUNION CAN BE OUR MEDAL.

1043
00:43:33,320 --> 00:43:36,320
R-I-I-I-IGHT.

1044
00:43:36,330 --> 00:43:38,330
HEY, WAIT UP!

1045
00:43:38,330 --> 00:43:41,830
NO, I'M GONNA BEAT YOU!

1046
00:43:41,830 --> 00:43:44,340
[ TRAIN RUMBLING ]

1047
00:43:44,330 --> 00:43:47,330
DID YOU KNOW
THAT MY MOM AND DAD

1048
00:43:47,340 --> 00:43:49,840
DON'T LET ME ON THE EL
WITHOUT THEM?

1049
00:43:49,840 --> 00:43:52,340
YEAH, BUT FATHER KELLY
AT THE CHURCH,

1050
00:43:52,340 --> 00:43:54,850
HE ALWAYS TALKS ABOUT
THIS RISK REWARD.

1051
00:43:54,840 --> 00:43:57,840
SO YOU'LL BE OKAY IF YOUR
PARENTS FIND OUT.

1052
00:43:57,850 --> 00:44:02,860
YOU'LL JUST EXPLAIN TO THEM THAT
THE RISK IS WORTH THE REWARD.

1053
00:44:02,850 --> 00:44:04,350
OKAY, ANYWAYS, LISTEN.

1054
00:44:04,350 --> 00:44:06,350
I HEARD BRUCE JENNER SAY

1055
00:44:06,360 --> 00:44:10,860
THAT THE KEY TO WINNING THE
DECATHLON IS TO STAY FOCUSED.

1056
00:44:10,860 --> 00:44:12,870
YOU STAY FOCUSED ON
THE DECATHLON,

1057
00:44:12,860 --> 00:44:14,860
FORGET
ABOUT EVERYTHING ELSE,

1058
00:44:14,860 --> 00:44:16,360
AND THEN, UH, YOU CAN, UH,

1059
00:44:16,370 --> 00:44:18,370
GET TO THE COMMUNION PART
OF IT.

1060
00:44:18,370 --> 00:44:20,870
<i>♪ IN THE SUMMERTIME
WHEN THE WEATHER IS HOT ♪</i>

1061
00:44:20,870 --> 00:44:23,880
<i>♪ YOU CAN STRETCH RIGHT UP
AND TOUCH THE SKY ♪</i>

1062
00:44:23,870 --> 00:44:25,870
<i>♪ WHEN THE WEATHER'S FINE ♪</i>

1063
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:28,880
<i>♪ YOU GOT WOMEN, YOU GOT WOMEN
ON YOUR MIND ♪</i>

1064
00:44:28,880 --> 00:44:31,380
<i>♪ HAVE A DRINK,
HAVE A DRIVE... ♪</i>

1065
00:44:31,380 --> 00:44:33,890
IF YOU SEE MY SISTER,
JUST START RUNNING.

1066
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:36,380
BUT HOW WILL I KNOW
IT'S YOUR SISTER?

1067
00:44:36,390 --> 00:44:37,390
<i>I'LL BE RUNNING.</i>

1068
00:44:37,390 --> 00:44:38,890
RIGHT.

1069
00:44:38,890 --> 00:44:41,390
<i>♪ ...IF HER DADDY'S POOR,
JUST DO WHAT YOU FEEL ♪</i>

1070
00:44:41,390 --> 00:44:43,400
<i>♪ SPEED ALONG THE LANE... ♪</i>

1071
00:44:43,390 --> 00:44:44,390
OOF!

1072
00:44:44,390 --> 00:44:47,390
YOU GOTTA WATCH WHERE
YOU'RE GOIN'.

1073
00:44:47,400 --> 00:44:49,400
<i>YOU OKAY?</i>

1074
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:54,410
THEY SEEM TO BE STARTING YOUNGER
AND YOUNGER THESE DAYS.

1075
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:56,400
<i>♪ ...WE'RE NOT DIRTY,
WE'RE NOT MEAN ♪</i>

1076
00:44:56,410 --> 00:44:58,910
<i>♪ WE LOVE EVERYBODY,
BUT WE DO AS WE PLEASE... ♪</i>

1077
00:44:58,910 --> 00:44:59,910
COME ON.

1078
00:44:59,910 --> 00:45:01,410
<i>LISTEN...</i>

1079
00:45:01,410 --> 00:45:02,920
YOU HAVE TO GET SERIOUS.

1080
00:45:03,410 --> 00:45:05,410
BRUCE JENNER IS FASTER,
STRONGER,

1081
00:45:05,420 --> 00:45:08,420
AND CAN JUMP HIGHER
THAN ANYONE ELSE I KNOW.

1082
00:45:08,420 --> 00:45:12,420
SO I FIGURE THAT THAT'S HOW
WE SHOULD DO THE DECATHLON.

1083
00:45:12,420 --> 00:45:13,930
OKAY, I'M FAST.

1084
00:45:13,920 --> 00:45:16,420
WELL, FIRST YOU HAVE TO BE
BAPTIZED.

1085
00:45:16,430 --> 00:45:18,930
[ GIGGLING ]

1086
00:45:18,930 --> 00:45:20,930
AHH!

1087
00:45:20,930 --> 00:45:22,940
AHH!

1088
00:45:23,430 --> 00:45:24,930
AMEN!

1089
00:45:24,930 --> 00:45:28,430
I THINK IT WOULD'VE BEEN EASIER
IF YOU WERE A BABY.

1090
00:45:28,940 --> 00:45:30,940
ON YOUR MARK...

1091
00:45:30,940 --> 00:45:32,950
GET SET...

1092
00:45:32,940 --> 00:45:33,940
GO!

1093
00:45:40,950 --> 00:45:43,460
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

1094
00:45:43,450 --> 00:45:45,450
ALL RIGHT!

1095
00:45:45,460 --> 00:45:46,460
GOOD JOB!

1096
00:45:46,460 --> 00:45:47,460
<i>THANKS.</i>

1097
00:45:47,960 --> 00:45:51,960
<i>ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE.</i>

1098
00:45:51,960 --> 00:45:56,470
<i>♪ ...WE'LL GO DRIVING
OR MAYBE WE'LL SETTLE DOWN ♪</i>

1099
00:45:56,470 --> 00:45:59,970
<i>TRY TO THROW PAST
THAT LINE.</i>

1100
00:45:59,970 --> 00:46:00,970
[ GRUNTS ]

1101
00:46:02,470 --> 00:46:06,480
WHOA.
THAT WAS A GOOD THROW.

1102
00:46:06,480 --> 00:46:09,480
SO, WHAT ELSE CAN WE DO?

1103
00:46:09,480 --> 00:46:13,490
<i>WELL, IN THE OLYMPICS,
I'VE SEEN THEM DO HURDLES.</i>

1104
00:46:13,480 --> 00:46:15,480
BUT WHAT COULD WE HURDLE?

1105
00:46:15,490 --> 00:46:17,990
[ SIGHS ]

1106
00:46:17,990 --> 00:46:19,990
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

1107
00:46:19,990 --> 00:46:21,490
GO FOR IT.

1108
00:46:23,990 --> 00:46:25,490
HEY!

1109
00:46:25,500 --> 00:46:27,500
HEY, YOU!

1110
00:46:27,500 --> 00:46:29,000
WHOA!

1111
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:30,500
[ LAUGHING ]

1112
00:46:30,500 --> 00:46:31,500
OH, SHOOT!

1113
00:46:36,010 --> 00:46:38,510
WHOA.

1114
00:46:38,510 --> 00:46:41,510
WE REALLY NEED THE RIGHT ROCK
<i>TO DO THIS.</i>

1115
00:46:41,510 --> 00:46:44,520
YOU WANT THE SURFACE TO BE FLAT
LIKE THIS.

1116
00:46:44,510 --> 00:46:48,010
MY RECORD'S, LIKE,
FIVE SKIPS.

1117
00:46:50,020 --> 00:46:53,030
OKAY, MAYBE THAT WAS
A LITTLE TOO HARD.

1118
00:46:53,520 --> 00:46:56,520
THIS ONE?

1119
00:46:56,530 --> 00:46:58,030
YEAH, YOU COULD TRY IT.

1120
00:46:58,030 --> 00:47:00,530
<i>MIGHT NOT WORK,
BUT YOU COULD TRY IT.</i>

1121
00:47:04,530 --> 00:47:07,530
THAT...
WAS A REALLY GOOD THROW.

1122
00:47:07,540 --> 00:47:11,540
I COULD BEAT IT,
I JUST NEED A REALLY GOOD ROCK.

1123
00:47:13,040 --> 00:47:15,540
NO. NO. NO.

1124
00:47:19,550 --> 00:47:22,050
THAT'S NO GOOD.

1125
00:47:26,560 --> 00:47:29,560
[ Chuckles ]
HEH HEH HEH.

1126
00:47:29,560 --> 00:47:31,060
YEAH, YEAH.

1127
00:47:31,060 --> 00:47:32,560
HOW YA DOIN'?

1128
00:47:32,560 --> 00:47:36,570
Danny: NO WONDER PEOPLE DIE
TRYING TO GET TO HEAVEN.

1129
00:47:36,570 --> 00:47:40,070
THE LAST ONE'S
GOTTA BE TOUGH.

1130
00:47:40,070 --> 00:47:41,570
I DON'T KNOW.

1131
00:47:41,570 --> 00:47:44,580
'CAUSE SOME OF THOSE
WERE REAL TOUGH.

1132
00:47:44,570 --> 00:47:48,070
YEAH, BUT THE LAST ONE'S GOTTA
BE REALLY, <i>REALLY TOUGH.</i>

1133
00:47:48,580 --> 00:47:52,080
SOMETHING THAT TAKES STRENGTH,
SPEED, AND COURAGE.

1134
00:47:52,080 --> 00:47:54,590
I DON'T KNOW.

1135
00:47:54,580 --> 00:47:57,080
SWIM OUT TO THE BUOY.

1136
00:47:57,590 --> 00:48:00,590
I CAN'T EVEN <i>SEE THE BUOY.</i>

1137
00:48:00,590 --> 00:48:03,600
I CAN'T GET THERE.

1138
00:48:03,590 --> 00:48:06,590
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO IF YOU WANT
TO WIN THE DECATHLON.

1139
00:48:15,610 --> 00:48:17,610
<i>GO AHEAD.</i>

1140
00:48:38,130 --> 00:48:41,630
[ GASPING ]

1141
00:48:50,140 --> 00:48:51,640
<i>Danny: HELP! I NEED HELP!</i>

1142
00:48:56,650 --> 00:48:59,150
YOU PASSED 9 OUT OF 10
TESTS.

1143
00:48:59,150 --> 00:49:01,150
GOD'S GOTTA BE HAPPY
WITH YOU.

1144
00:49:01,150 --> 00:49:04,660
YEAH, BUT I DON'T KNOW IF I'M
GONNA PASS THE LAST ONE.

1145
00:49:04,650 --> 00:49:06,150
THAT'S TOUGH.

1146
00:49:06,160 --> 00:49:09,160
I REALLY WANT TO PASS
<i>THE DECATHLON.</i>

1147
00:49:09,160 --> 00:49:10,660
I WANT TO GO TO HEAVEN.

1148
00:49:16,170 --> 00:49:18,670
<i>Pete: DO KIDS DIE
FROM WHAT YOU HAVE?</i>

1149
00:49:18,670 --> 00:49:21,670
<i>WELL, I HEARD SOME ADULTS
WHISPERING ABOUT IT.</i>

1150
00:49:21,670 --> 00:49:24,680
ADULTS ALWAYS GET QUIET WHEN
THEY TALK ABOUT DEATH.

1151
00:49:24,670 --> 00:49:27,670
SOMETIMES I HEAR MY PARENTS TALK
ABOUT IT LATE AT NIGHT.

1152
00:49:28,180 --> 00:49:29,680
SOMETIMES THEY START TO CRY.

1153
00:49:29,680 --> 00:49:33,690
I DON'T WANT THEM TO FEEL SAD
IF I DIE.

1154
00:49:33,970 --> 00:49:37,190
WELL,
THERE'S OUR LITTLE MAN.

1155
00:49:37,190 --> 00:49:39,690
THANKS FOR JOINING US.

1156
00:49:42,690 --> 00:49:45,200
[ SPEAKING HEBREW ]

1157
00:49:45,190 --> 00:49:48,190
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

1158
00:49:48,700 --> 00:49:50,700
THANKING GOD FOR THE FOOD.

1159
00:49:50,700 --> 00:49:53,210
YEAH, BUT WHAT WAS THAT YOU DID
AS I BEGAN THE PRAYER?

1160
00:49:53,200 --> 00:49:55,200
OH, YOU MEAN THIS?

1161
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:58,200
YEAH.

1162
00:49:58,210 --> 00:50:00,710
WELL, IT'S LIKE PICKING UP
A PHONE AND CALLING GOD.

1163
00:50:00,710 --> 00:50:02,710
I JUST WANTED TO MAKE SURE
HE WAS THERE TO HEAR YOU.

1164
00:50:02,710 --> 00:50:05,220
OKAY.

1165
00:50:07,720 --> 00:50:09,720
YOU KNOW, THIS QUEST
FOR HEAVEN --

1166
00:50:10,220 --> 00:50:13,230
IT'S, UH, IT'S A GOOD THING,
OF COURSE,

1167
00:50:13,220 --> 00:50:17,220
BUT AS JEWISH PEOPLE, WE HAVE
OUR OWN RITUALS AND CUSTOMS...

1168
00:50:17,230 --> 00:50:19,230
DIFFERENT THAN PETE'S.

1169
00:50:19,230 --> 00:50:20,730
YEAH, I KNOW.

1170
00:50:20,730 --> 00:50:25,740
I TAUGHT PETE SOME OF THEM,
BUT I LIKE THIS ONE.

1171
00:50:25,740 --> 00:50:26,740
I SEE.

1172
00:50:26,740 --> 00:50:29,240
[ SPEAKING HEBREW RAPIDLY ]

1173
00:50:29,240 --> 00:50:32,740
<i>BUT LET'S, UH...</i>

1174
00:50:32,740 --> 00:50:34,750
LET'S MAYBE DO THIS LESS...

1175
00:50:34,740 --> 00:50:36,240
AS IN NOT AT ALL.

1176
00:50:36,250 --> 00:50:38,250
OKAY.

1177
00:50:38,250 --> 00:50:40,250
THANKS.

1178
00:50:47,260 --> 00:50:49,260
THERE YOU GO.

1179
00:50:49,260 --> 00:50:51,760
<i>IT PROBABLY WOULDN'T BE GOOD
FOR BUSINESS</i>

1180
00:50:51,760 --> 00:50:54,270
<i>IF THE RABBI'S SON CONVERTS
TO CHRISTIANITY.</i>

1181
00:50:54,260 --> 00:50:55,260
I WOULDN'T THINK SO.

1182
00:50:55,260 --> 00:50:58,260
NO.

1183
00:50:58,270 --> 00:51:00,270
KENNY, MAYBE THIS IS GOING
TOO FAR.

1184
00:51:00,770 --> 00:51:02,270
WHAT WOULD YOU HAVE ME DO,

1185
00:51:02,270 --> 00:51:04,780
TELL OUR SON HE CAN'T GO OUT
AND PLAY WITH PETE?

1186
00:51:04,770 --> 00:51:06,270
WOULD THAT MAKE YOU HAPPY?

1187
00:51:06,780 --> 00:51:08,280
I DON'T THINK IT'S ABOUT
MAKING ME HAPPY.

1188
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:10,280
I THINK IT'S ABOUT YOU BENDING
OVER BACKWARDS

1189
00:51:10,280 --> 00:51:11,780
NOT TO MAKE WAVES
WITH YOUR SON.

1190
00:51:11,780 --> 00:51:13,290
MAKE WAVES.

1191
00:51:13,280 --> 00:51:15,780
I THOUGHT WE WERE GONNA LET OUR
CHILDREN MAKE CHOICES IN LIFE,

1192
00:51:16,290 --> 00:51:18,290
THAT WE WERE GONNA TRY TO BE
A LITTLE BIT DIFFERENT

1193
00:51:18,290 --> 00:51:20,290
THAN OUR PARENTS WERE
<i>WITH US.</i>

1194
00:51:20,290 --> 00:51:22,290
LEAVE MY PARENTS
OUT OF THIS.

1195
00:51:22,290 --> 00:51:24,300
WAS I ALONE WHEN WE TALKED
<i>ABOUT THIS?</i>

1196
00:51:24,290 --> 00:51:26,790
NO, BUT I DON'T THINK
THIS IS THE TIME

1197
00:51:26,800 --> 00:51:28,800
FOR OUR CHILD
TO BE MAKING THESE CHOICES.

1198
00:51:28,800 --> 00:51:31,800
OR MAYBE
IT'S THE BEST TIME.

1199
00:51:31,800 --> 00:51:35,810
<i>WHY? SO DANNY CAN COVER ALL
OF HIS BASES?</i>

1200
00:51:36,310 --> 00:51:39,310
IT'S NOT ABOUT
COVERING BASES.

1201
00:51:39,310 --> 00:51:43,320
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
OUR SON WENT OUT...

1202
00:51:43,310 --> 00:51:46,310
ENJOYING HIMSELF...
PLAYING...

1203
00:51:46,320 --> 00:51:47,320
<i>LIKE A BOY?</i>

1204
00:51:47,320 --> 00:51:49,820
NOT LIKE A SICK BOY, JUST...

1205
00:51:49,820 --> 00:51:52,320
A BOY.

1206
00:51:58,830 --> 00:51:59,830
GOOD LUCK.

1207
00:51:59,830 --> 00:52:01,830
THANKS. I'LL NEED IT.

1208
00:52:01,830 --> 00:52:03,340
YEAH, I KNOW.

1209
00:52:21,850 --> 00:52:24,360
<i>HELP, PETE! HELP!</i>

1210
00:52:29,860 --> 00:52:31,360
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

1211
00:52:31,360 --> 00:52:36,370
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'RE GONNA MAKE
IT, AND THEN YOU DON'T.

1212
00:52:36,370 --> 00:52:37,370
I DON'T KNOW.

1213
00:52:38,870 --> 00:52:42,370
WELL, YOU MAKE IT BACK FINE
WITH ME.

1214
00:52:42,370 --> 00:52:45,380
I KNOW.

1215
00:52:45,370 --> 00:52:47,370
SO, THEN, WHAT'S WRONG?

1216
00:52:47,380 --> 00:52:50,380
WELL, I LOOK UP TO SEE
WHERE THE BUOY IS,

1217
00:52:50,880 --> 00:52:52,380
AND I CAN'T SEE IT.

1218
00:52:52,380 --> 00:52:56,390
AND THEN I REALIZE HOW FAR OUT
I AM, AND THEN, WELL...

1219
00:52:56,390 --> 00:52:58,390
WHAT IF I GO WITH YOU?

1220
00:52:58,390 --> 00:53:00,890
UM, NO.
I GOTTA DO IT ALONE.

1221
00:53:00,890 --> 00:53:02,390
MMM...

1222
00:53:02,390 --> 00:53:04,900
BUT WHAT IF YOU DON'T
LOOK UP?

1223
00:53:04,890 --> 00:53:07,390
BUT THEN I DON'T KNOW
WHERE I AM.

1224
00:53:07,400 --> 00:53:09,900
DON'T WORRY.
WE'LL FIGURE THIS OUT.

1225
00:53:18,910 --> 00:53:19,910
I CAN SEE FINE.

1226
00:53:19,910 --> 00:53:23,420
I CAN SEE IT FROM HERE,
BUT WHEN I GET IN THE WATER,

1227
00:53:23,410 --> 00:53:24,910
I CAN'T SEE IT,

1228
00:53:24,910 --> 00:53:27,910
AND THEN EVERYTHING STARTS
GETTING REALLY FAST,

1229
00:53:27,920 --> 00:53:29,920
AND I CAN'T GO
ANY FURTHER.

1230
00:53:39,430 --> 00:53:41,930
STAY RIGHT HERE AND WATCH ME
SWIM TO THE BUOY.

1231
00:53:41,930 --> 00:53:44,940
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

1232
00:54:05,960 --> 00:54:07,960
51...

1233
00:54:07,960 --> 00:54:09,960
52...

1234
00:54:09,960 --> 00:54:11,960
53...

1235
00:54:11,960 --> 00:54:13,970
<i>54...</i>

1236
00:54:14,460 --> 00:54:15,960
<i>55.</i>

1237
00:54:15,970 --> 00:54:19,470
LISTEN, ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS COUNT YOUR STROKES.

1238
00:54:19,970 --> 00:54:23,480
IT TOOK ME 50 STROKES THERE
AND 55 STROKES BACK.

1239
00:54:23,470 --> 00:54:25,470
YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE
TO LOOK UP.

1240
00:54:25,470 --> 00:54:26,970
CAN YOU COUNT TO 50?

1241
00:54:26,980 --> 00:54:27,980
YEAH.

1242
00:54:27,980 --> 00:54:29,480
I'M A LITTLE BIGGER,

1243
00:54:29,480 --> 00:54:31,980
SO IT MIGHT TAKE YOU
A FEW MORE STROKES.

1244
00:54:31,980 --> 00:54:32,980
CAN YOU COUNT TO 60?

1245
00:54:32,980 --> 00:54:34,490
YEP.

1246
00:54:34,980 --> 00:54:36,980
WELL, THEN JUST COUNT TO 60
STROKES, AND THEN SWIM BACK.

1247
00:54:36,990 --> 00:54:38,490
OKAY. I CAN DO THAT.

1248
00:54:38,990 --> 00:54:40,990
BUT LET'S DO IT TOMORROW.

1249
00:54:40,990 --> 00:54:45,000
<i>MEET ME UNDER THE STAIRS
AT THE SYNAGOGUE.</i>

1250
00:54:44,990 --> 00:54:46,490
RIGHT. TOMORROW.

1251
00:54:46,500 --> 00:54:50,000
TOMORROW YOU COMPLETE
THE DECATHLON.

1252
00:55:03,510 --> 00:55:06,010
DANNY SAID
I MIGHT FIND YOU HERE.

1253
00:55:09,520 --> 00:55:13,530
WELL, UH, I DON'T KNOW HOW HE
KNEW I WOULD BE HERE.

1254
00:55:13,520 --> 00:55:17,520
HE SAID TELL YOU HE COULDN'T
COMPLETE THE DECATHLON TODAY.

1255
00:55:17,530 --> 00:55:21,030
WELL, TELL HIM I CAN MEET HIM
TOMORROW.

1256
00:55:21,030 --> 00:55:23,030
TOMORROW'S NO GOOD,
EITHER.

1257
00:55:23,030 --> 00:55:26,540
HE'S GOT TO SEE THE DOCTOR
ABOUT HIS CANCER.

1258
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:38,040
I THINK HE'S FINE.

1259
00:55:38,050 --> 00:55:40,550
I THINK SO, TOO.

1260
00:55:43,050 --> 00:55:46,560
ARE THEY GONNA GIVE HIM
ANY MORE OF THAT MEDICINE

1261
00:55:46,560 --> 00:55:48,560
THAT MAKES HIM
LOSE HIS HAIR?

1262
00:55:48,560 --> 00:55:51,060
I DON'T KNOW.

1263
00:55:51,060 --> 00:55:52,560
I'M NOT A DOCTOR.

1264
00:55:52,560 --> 00:55:56,570
MY OLDEST BROTHER WANTS TO
BECOME A DOCTOR.

1265
00:55:56,570 --> 00:55:58,570
YEAH?

1266
00:55:58,570 --> 00:56:00,570
COULD ALWAYS USE ANOTHER
GOOD DOCTOR.

1267
00:56:00,570 --> 00:56:02,570
MY DAD SAYS THEY PLAY
TOO MUCH GOLF,

1268
00:56:02,570 --> 00:56:04,080
AND THEY CHARGE
LIKE BASTARDS.

1269
00:56:07,080 --> 00:56:09,080
SEAMUS SAYS IT'S OKAY
TO SAY SWEAR WORDS

1270
00:56:09,080 --> 00:56:12,080
AS LONG AS YOU'RE SAYING WHAT
THE PERSON BEFORE YOU SAID.

1271
00:56:12,080 --> 00:56:16,590
SEAMUS SOUNDS LIKE HE'LL BE
A GOOD JOURNALIST SOMEDAY.

1272
00:56:16,590 --> 00:56:19,590
TELL ME ABOUT
YOUR OLDER BROTHER.

1273
00:56:19,590 --> 00:56:23,090
IS HE, UH, STUDYING MEDICINE
IN SCHOOL?

1274
00:56:23,090 --> 00:56:26,600
NO, HE CAN'T AFFORD IT.

1275
00:56:26,600 --> 00:56:29,100
MEDICINE'S VERY EXPENSIVE.

1276
00:56:29,100 --> 00:56:34,110
CERTAINLY WORTH IT, THOUGH,
IF YOU WORK HARD.

1277
00:56:34,100 --> 00:56:38,600
RABBI, WHEN DO YOU THINK DANNY
WILL BE BETTER?

1278
00:56:38,610 --> 00:56:42,110
[ SIGHS ]

1279
00:56:42,110 --> 00:56:44,620
I THINK THAT ONE'S
IN GOD'S HANDS.

1280
00:56:44,610 --> 00:56:46,610
WELL, YOU'RE CLOSE TO GOD.

1281
00:56:46,620 --> 00:56:49,620
HOPEFULLY THAT RUBS OFF
A LITTLE ON DANNY.

1282
00:56:49,620 --> 00:56:52,120
I REALLY HOPE HE GETS BETTER
<i>SOON.</i>

1283
00:56:52,120 --> 00:56:56,130
WE'VE GOT SOME UNFINISHED
BUSINESS TO HANDLE.

1284
00:56:56,130 --> 00:57:01,630
I CERTAINLY HOPE YOU GET TO TAKE
CARE OF THAT BUSINESS.

1285
00:57:01,630 --> 00:57:05,640
FOR NOW, WHAT DANNY NEEDS
IS OUR PRAYERS.

1286
00:57:05,630 --> 00:57:06,630
<i>OKAY.</i>

1287
00:57:06,640 --> 00:57:09,140
I'LL PRAY TO JESUS,
AND YOU PRAY TO GOD,

1288
00:57:09,140 --> 00:57:11,640
AND HOPEFULLY ONE OF THE TWO
WILL ANSWER.

1289
00:57:11,640 --> 00:57:12,640
THAT'S A DEAL.

1290
00:57:12,640 --> 00:57:16,650
SEE YOU LATER,
RABBI JACOBSEN.

1291
00:57:20,520 --> 00:57:21,650
OH, THAT WAS GOOD.

1292
00:57:21,650 --> 00:57:23,150
THANK YOU, DEAR.

1293
00:57:23,150 --> 00:57:24,660
YOU KNOW, UM,
THE RABBI CALLED

1294
00:57:25,150 --> 00:57:27,150
AND SAID HE WANTED TO STOP BY
AFTER DINNER,

1295
00:57:27,160 --> 00:57:28,660
AND I SAID IT WAS OKAY.

1296
00:57:28,660 --> 00:57:30,160
RABBI?
MM-HMM.

1297
00:57:30,160 --> 00:57:33,160
JEWISH PEOPLE GO OVERBOARD
WITH THIS GRATITUDE STUFF,
DON'T THEY?

1298
00:57:33,160 --> 00:57:35,170
HONEY, I DON'T THINK IT HAS
ANYTHING TO DO

1299
00:57:35,660 --> 00:57:36,660
WITH HIM BEING JEWISH.

1300
00:57:36,670 --> 00:57:38,670
<i>HE'S JUST SAYING THANK YOU.</i>

1301
00:57:38,670 --> 00:57:39,670
WHERE'S KNUCKLEHEAD?

1302
00:57:39,670 --> 00:57:41,670
<i>MOM,
WHERE DOES THIS DISH GO?</i>

1303
00:57:42,170 --> 00:57:44,180
HE CALLED,
HE SAID HE'D BE LATE.

1304
00:57:44,170 --> 00:57:45,670
HE CALLED, ALL RIGHT?

1305
00:57:45,670 --> 00:57:47,170
AT LEAST HE CALLED.

1306
00:57:47,180 --> 00:57:51,180
PROBABLY SITTING ON HIS CAN
IN THAT LIFEGUARD TOWER

1307
00:57:51,180 --> 00:57:52,680
READING A BOOK.

1308
00:57:52,680 --> 00:57:54,190
DIRTY BOOK.

1309
00:57:54,180 --> 00:57:56,180
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

1310
00:57:56,190 --> 00:57:57,190
COME IN.

1311
00:57:57,690 --> 00:57:59,190
HE'S AT THE DOOR.
YOU DON'T YELL.

1312
00:57:59,190 --> 00:58:00,690
WHAT?
OH, HI.

1313
00:58:00,690 --> 00:58:02,690
HI. RABBI JACOBSEN.
MARGARET O'MALLEY.

1314
00:58:02,690 --> 00:58:04,200
HEY, RABBI.
HOW ARE YOU?

1315
00:58:04,190 --> 00:58:06,690
GOOD, GOOD, GOOD.
I'M SORRY TO INTERRUPT YOU.

1316
00:58:06,700 --> 00:58:08,700
NO, NO. WOULD YOU LIKE
SOMETHING TO EAT?

1317
00:58:09,200 --> 00:58:11,200
I CAN MAKE YOU A PLATE.
OH, THANKS, NO.

1318
00:58:11,200 --> 00:58:13,710
MY WIFE THINKS IF I EAT
ANOTHER WOMAN'S COOKING,

1319
00:58:13,700 --> 00:58:16,200
IT'S A FORM OF ADULTERY,
SO I SHOULDN'T.

1320
00:58:16,210 --> 00:58:18,710
BUT I BROUGHT SOMETHING
FOR AFTER THE MEAL.

1321
00:58:18,710 --> 00:58:21,210
OH. ALL RIGHTY.
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME COFFEE?

1322
00:58:21,210 --> 00:58:23,720
THAT'D BE GREAT.
THAT'D BE GREAT, YEAH, THANKS.

1323
00:58:23,710 --> 00:58:24,710
SIT.
OKAY.

1324
00:58:24,710 --> 00:58:26,710
SO, HOW'S YOUR, UH,
HOW'S YOUR LITTLE BOY?

1325
00:58:27,220 --> 00:58:28,220
OH, HE'S GOOD. THANKS.

1326
00:58:28,220 --> 00:58:31,220
YEAH, WE'RE GOING TOMORROW
FOR THE MONTHLY CHECKUP,

1327
00:58:31,220 --> 00:58:33,730
AND HOPEFULLY IT'LL BE
SIX MONTHS REMISSION.

1328
00:58:33,720 --> 00:58:35,220
OH, GOOD, GOOD.
WE HOPE SO, TOO.

1329
00:58:35,220 --> 00:58:36,720
OH, THANKS, THANKS.

1330
00:58:36,730 --> 00:58:37,730
<i>HERE YOU GO.</i>

1331
00:58:37,730 --> 00:58:40,730
<i>OH, GREAT.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.</i>

1332
00:58:40,730 --> 00:58:42,230
SO WHAT'S GOING ON?

1333
00:58:42,230 --> 00:58:44,740
OH, WELL, YOU PROBABLY REMEMBER
I MENTIONED TO YOU

1334
00:58:44,730 --> 00:58:46,730
THAT THE SYNAGOGUE WOULD LIKE
TO FORMALLY THANK YOU

1335
00:58:46,740 --> 00:58:48,240
FOR YOUR BRAVERY.

1336
00:58:48,240 --> 00:58:49,240
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO.

1337
00:58:49,240 --> 00:58:50,740
THERE'S NO NEED FOR THAT.

1338
00:58:51,240 --> 00:58:53,750
I TOLD YOU, YOU KNOW,
WE'RE JUST DOING OUR JOB.

1339
00:58:53,740 --> 00:58:57,240
<i>AND I HAVE A STANDING ORDER
NOT TO DISAGREE WITH A MAN
UNDER HIS OWN ROOF,</i>

1340
00:58:57,250 --> 00:59:00,250
BUT, UM, YOU RISKED YOUR LIFE
TO SAVE MY SON'S LIFE,

1341
00:59:00,250 --> 00:59:01,750
AND IF NOT FOR THE EXPLOSION,

1342
00:59:01,750 --> 00:59:04,760
YOU WOULD'VE MARCHED BACK
IN TO GET ESTHER --

1343
00:59:04,750 --> 00:59:07,750
AGAINST THE WISHES OF YOUR
PARTNERS, I SHOULD ADD.

1344
00:59:07,760 --> 00:59:09,260
<i>OH, HONEY --
EXCUSE ME, RABBI.</i>

1345
00:59:09,260 --> 00:59:10,760
<i>THIS IS OUR OLDEST BOY
PATRICK.</i>

1346
00:59:10,760 --> 00:59:12,760
THIS IS
RABBI JACOBSEN.
PATRICK.

1347
00:59:12,760 --> 00:59:15,270
PETE TOLD ME ALL ABOUT YOU.
IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU.

1348
00:59:15,260 --> 00:59:16,760
YEAH,
IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU.

1349
00:59:16,770 --> 00:59:19,270
I, UM, I HEARD ABOUT YOUR LOSS.
I'M VERY SORRY.

1350
00:59:19,270 --> 00:59:22,270
OH, THANKS, YEAH.
I WAS JUST TELLING
YOUR FATHER THAT --

1351
00:59:22,270 --> 00:59:24,780
IN FACT, YOU MAY WANT TO JOIN
US, IF THAT'S OKAY.

1352
00:59:24,770 --> 00:59:28,270
PETE TOLD ME ABOUT YOUR INTEREST
IN STUDYING MEDICINE IN COLLEGE,

1353
00:59:28,280 --> 00:59:30,780
AND OUR SYNAGOGUE GIVES
SCHOLARSHIPS EVERY YEAR

1354
00:59:30,780 --> 00:59:31,780
TO A FEW STUDENTS,

1355
00:59:32,280 --> 00:59:34,290
AND THIS YEAR,
IN HONOR OF ESTHER SIMON,

1356
00:59:34,280 --> 00:59:36,780
WE'RE GONNA GIVE A FULL
SCHOLARSHIP TO ONE STUDENT.

1357
00:59:36,790 --> 00:59:39,290
AND I RECOMMENDED TO THE BOARD,
AND THEY AGREED,

1358
00:59:39,290 --> 00:59:41,290
THAT PATRICK BE THE RECIPIENT
OF THE SCHOLARSHIP.

1359
00:59:41,290 --> 00:59:43,800
THANK YOU, RABBI.

1360
00:59:43,790 --> 00:59:45,290
HONEY?

1361
00:59:47,300 --> 00:59:50,800
RABBI, THAT IS AN EXTREMELY
<i>KIND OFFER,</i>

1362
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:53,810
BUT, UNFORTUNATELY,
ONE THAT WE CANNOT ACCEPT.

1363
00:59:58,810 --> 01:00:00,810
<i>OH, WELL, I --</i>

1364
01:00:00,810 --> 01:00:03,820
ON BEHALF OF MY CONGREGATION
AND FAMILY,

1365
01:00:03,810 --> 01:00:07,810
I CERTAINLY HOPE YOU CAN
RECONSIDER ACCEPTING IT.

1366
01:00:07,820 --> 01:00:09,820
OTHER MEN RISKED THEIR LIVES
THAT DAY AT YOUR HOUSE.

1367
01:00:10,320 --> 01:00:11,820
IT WASN'T JUST ME.
<i>UNDERSTOOD.</i>

1368
01:00:11,820 --> 01:00:14,330
<i>IT JUST SEEMED A BIT MORE
PERSONAL THAN OFFERING UP, SAY,</i>

1369
01:00:14,320 --> 01:00:16,320
A STATUE TO THE ENTIRE
FIRE DEPARTMENT.

1370
01:00:16,330 --> 01:00:18,330
I SPOKE TO YOUR CHIEF.
HE APPROVED IT.

1371
01:00:18,330 --> 01:00:20,330
YOU SPOKE TO MY CHIEF?
<i>WELL, YES.</i>

1372
01:00:20,330 --> 01:00:22,330
<i>I HAD TO MAKE SURE THAT IT
WAS WITHIN THE RULES.</i>

1373
01:00:22,330 --> 01:00:25,340
[ SIGHS ] THE BOARD GIVES
ONE SCHOLARSHIP,

1374
01:00:25,830 --> 01:00:29,330
PETE MENTIONED PATRICK'S DESIRE,
AND I RECOMMENDED PATRICK.

1375
01:00:29,340 --> 01:00:31,340
I IMAGINE THEY WANT TO
GIVE IT TO HIM

1376
01:00:31,340 --> 01:00:33,340
IN A REAL PUBLIC CEREMONY.

1377
01:00:33,340 --> 01:00:34,350
<i>I IMAGINE SO.</i>

1378
01:00:34,340 --> 01:00:37,340
<i>BE GOOD AS A PUBLIC SHOW,
YES.</i>

1379
01:00:37,350 --> 01:00:39,850
FREE PUBLICITY FOR THE TEMPLE,
NO DOUBT.

1380
01:00:39,850 --> 01:00:41,350
<i>Margaret: JOSEPH.
WHAT?</i>

1381
01:00:41,350 --> 01:00:43,860
<i>WELL, THAT'S TOTALLY
INAPPROPRIATE.</i>

1382
01:00:43,850 --> 01:00:45,850
MR. O'MALLEY,
BOTH OF OUR RELIGIONS

1383
01:00:45,850 --> 01:00:47,350
ARE PRACTICED IN PUBLIC,

1384
01:00:47,360 --> 01:00:49,860
AND, YES, THERE ARE CEREMONIES
AND RITUALS.

1385
01:00:49,860 --> 01:00:52,360
THIS SCHOLARSHIP
ISN'T ABOUT FREE PUBLICITY.

1386
01:00:52,360 --> 01:00:55,370
IT'S ABOUT DOING GOOD, HONORING
GOOD, THANKING GOOD.

1387
01:00:55,360 --> 01:00:57,860
<i>I DON'T MEAN TO DISRESPECT YOU
OR YOUR FAMILY</i>

1388
01:00:58,370 --> 01:01:01,870
OR DISHONOR THE MEMORY
OF ESTHER SIMON.

1389
01:01:01,870 --> 01:01:02,870
<i>OF COURSE NOT.</i>

1390
01:01:03,370 --> 01:01:04,880
RABBI, THANK YOU
FOR STOPPING OVER.

1391
01:01:05,370 --> 01:01:06,870
MY SON PETE
HAS A BIG MOUTH,

1392
01:01:06,880 --> 01:01:08,880
AND MY FAMILY DOESN'T NEED
YOUR HANDOUTS.

1393
01:01:08,880 --> 01:01:10,880
WE THANK YOU
FOR YOUR KINDNESS.
JOE.

1394
01:01:11,380 --> 01:01:12,880
POP,
YOU CAN'T DO THAT TO ME.

1395
01:01:12,880 --> 01:01:15,890
YOU WILL SHUT YOUR MOUTH.

1396
01:01:15,880 --> 01:01:18,880
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

1397
01:01:18,890 --> 01:01:20,390
HEY...

1398
01:01:20,390 --> 01:01:22,390
WHERE THE HECK
DO YOU GET OFF

1399
01:01:22,390 --> 01:01:24,900
COMING INTO MY HOUSE
LIKE THAT, HUH?

1400
01:01:24,890 --> 01:01:26,390
I GOT MY SON ASKING ME,

1401
01:01:26,400 --> 01:01:28,900
"IS JESUS REALLY
THE SON OF GOD?"

1402
01:01:28,900 --> 01:01:29,900
HE'S 8!

1403
01:01:29,900 --> 01:01:32,400
WELL, THEN, IT SOUNDS LIKE
WE'RE IN THIS TOGETHER.

1404
01:01:32,400 --> 01:01:34,910
MY SON'S ASKING WHY HE CAN'T
MAKE THE SIGN OF THE CROSS

1405
01:01:34,900 --> 01:01:35,900
BEFORE HE PRAYS TO GOD.

1406
01:01:35,900 --> 01:01:38,400
MY CONGREGATION IS WONDERING
IF I'M TURNING INTO A RABBI

1407
01:01:38,410 --> 01:01:39,910
FOR JEWS FOR JESUS.

1408
01:01:39,910 --> 01:01:42,410
THE IRONY, OF COURSE, IS
THAT I DON'T THINK JESUS
WAS THE SON OF GOD!

1409
01:01:42,410 --> 01:01:44,920
YOU PREACH THAT TO <i>YOUR
PEOPLE. YOU KEEP IT OUT
OF MY HOUSE, ALL RIGHT?</i>

1410
01:01:44,910 --> 01:01:46,410
YOUR SON CAME TO <i>ME, OKAY?</i>

1411
01:01:46,420 --> 01:01:48,920
HE CAME TO ME TO ASK
IF HE COULD HELP JEWS --

1412
01:01:49,420 --> 01:01:50,920
<i>HELP SAVE JEWS
FROM GOING TO HELL!</i>

1413
01:01:51,420 --> 01:01:52,420
<i>HE CAME TO ME!</i>

1414
01:01:52,420 --> 01:01:54,930
YOU! GET BACK INSIDE!

1415
01:01:57,430 --> 01:02:00,430
IF SOMEONE COMES TO MY HOUSE
LIKE THAT,

1416
01:02:00,430 --> 01:02:02,930
I <i>POLITELY THROW HIM OUT
ON HIS ASS!</i>

1417
01:02:02,930 --> 01:02:04,440
<i>ON HIS ASS!
GOOD, I'LL REMEMBER THAT.</i>

1418
01:02:04,430 --> 01:02:06,930
"YOU DISAGREE WITH ME,
YOU'RE OUT ON YOUR ASS."

1419
01:02:06,940 --> 01:02:09,940
YOU KNOW, IT'S A GOOD THING
IT DIDN'T DETER YOUR ST. PAUL
WHEN THE ROMANS THREW HIM OUT

1420
01:02:09,940 --> 01:02:11,440
OR ST. PATRICK IN IRELAND
WITH THE SNAKES.

1421
01:02:11,440 --> 01:02:12,940
OH, DON'T START WITH THAT!

1422
01:02:12,940 --> 01:02:14,950
THROWING ST. PATRICK
BACK IN MY FACE!

1423
01:02:14,940 --> 01:02:16,940
THIS AIN'T
A BIBLE-STUDY GROUP, PAL!

1424
01:02:16,950 --> 01:02:18,950
[ SIGHS ]

1425
01:02:21,950 --> 01:02:23,450
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

1426
01:02:23,450 --> 01:02:25,960
POP, ARE YOU TOO PROUD
TO LET ME ACCEPT IT?

1427
01:02:25,950 --> 01:02:28,950
FIRST OF ALL, YOU HAVEN'T
DONE ANYTHING TO DESERVE IT,

1428
01:02:28,960 --> 01:02:32,960
AND SECONDLY, I AM NOT
GETTING INVOLVED IN HIS
PUBLICITY STUNT, ALL RIGHT?

1429
01:02:32,960 --> 01:02:34,970
JOE, I DON'T THINK
IT'S A PUBLICITY STUNT.

1430
01:02:34,960 --> 01:02:37,960
<i>I THINK IT'S AN ACT
OF KINDNESS IN RETURN
FOR AN ACT OF KINDNESS.</i>

1431
01:02:37,970 --> 01:02:40,970
I TOLD YOU NOTHING
GOOD WOULD COME OF
HIM GOING OVER THERE.

1432
01:02:40,970 --> 01:02:41,970
PETE!

1433
01:02:41,970 --> 01:02:43,470
GET IN HERE RIGHT NOW!

1434
01:02:43,470 --> 01:02:45,980
HONEY, PLEASE DON'T START
YELLING AT HIM.

1435
01:02:45,970 --> 01:02:49,470
WHAT DID HE TELL
THE RABBI -- THAT WE DON'T
HAVE ENOUGH FOOD TO EAT?

1436
01:02:49,480 --> 01:02:53,480
WELL, THEN MAYBE THE RABBI CAN
START A FOOD DRIVE FOR THIS
FAMILY, HOW 'BOUT THAT?

1437
01:02:53,480 --> 01:02:56,990
WHAT'D I TELL YOU ABOUT
NOT GOING TO THAT TEMPLE? HUH?

1438
01:02:56,990 --> 01:02:58,990
I'M ON A QUEST
TO GET DANNY INTO HEAVEN.

1439
01:02:59,490 --> 01:03:00,490
AND I'M ALMOST THERE.

1440
01:03:00,490 --> 01:03:02,990
ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE ON THE ROAD
TO HELL, MY FRIEND.

1441
01:03:02,990 --> 01:03:04,000
NOW GO TO YOUR ROOM
JOE...

1442
01:03:04,490 --> 01:03:05,990
AND DON'T COME OUT
UNTIL I TELL YOU TO.

1443
01:03:05,990 --> 01:03:06,990
WHAT?

1444
01:03:07,000 --> 01:03:08,500
<i>DON'T TELL HIM
THINGS LIKE THAT.</i>

1445
01:03:09,000 --> 01:03:10,500
I JUST WANTED
TO DO THE RIGHT THING.

1446
01:03:10,500 --> 01:03:12,500
THE RIGHT THING. YOU KNOW
WHAT THE RIGHT THING IS?

1447
01:03:12,500 --> 01:03:15,510
IS WHEN YOUR MOTHER
TELLS YOU SOMETHING
OR WHEN <i>I TELL YOU SOMETHING.</i>

1448
01:03:15,500 --> 01:03:19,500
YOU DON'T WORRY
ABOUT JEWS, YOU DON'T
WORRY ABOUT CATHOLICS.

1449
01:03:19,510 --> 01:03:21,010
YOU WORRY ABOUT <i>ME.</i>

1450
01:03:21,010 --> 01:03:25,020
NOW GO TO YOUR ROOM
AND GO THERE UNTIL
I TELL YOU TO COME OUT!

1451
01:03:34,520 --> 01:03:37,020
POP, I'M GONNA GO
SEE THAT RABBI MYSELF,

1452
01:03:37,030 --> 01:03:39,030
AND I'M GONNA
WORK OUT A DEAL, OKAY?

1453
01:03:39,030 --> 01:03:41,530
OVER MY DEAD BODY.

1454
01:03:41,530 --> 01:03:44,040
THIS IS NOT ABOUT <i>YOU.</i>

1455
01:03:44,030 --> 01:03:46,030
IT'S NOT ABOUT KINDNESS.

1456
01:03:46,030 --> 01:03:49,030
IT'S ABOUT THE JEWS
<i>GETTING PUBLICITY</i>

1457
01:03:49,040 --> 01:03:52,540
FOR HELPING OUT SOME POOR
IRISH CATHOLIC FAMILY

1458
01:03:53,040 --> 01:03:54,550
SO THEY CAN GET ON THE NEWS

1459
01:03:54,540 --> 01:03:57,040
AND EVERYBODY CAN SAY
HOW NICE IT IS OF THEM

1460
01:03:57,050 --> 01:04:00,050
THAT THEY SHARE THEIR MONEY
WITH THESE POOR SLOBS.

1461
01:04:00,050 --> 01:04:04,560
<i>WHY DO YOU HAVE TO BE
SO CYNICAL ABOUT THIS, HUH?</i>

1462
01:04:04,550 --> 01:04:06,050
Y-Y-YOU HAVE TOO MUCH PRIDE

1463
01:04:06,560 --> 01:04:09,060
TO LET THIS MAN HELP ME OUT,
HELP YOUR SON OUT?

1464
01:04:09,060 --> 01:04:11,060
MAYBE IF YOU HAD
A LITTLE <i>MORE PRIDE --</i>

1465
01:04:11,560 --> 01:04:13,060
POP, I HAVE HEARD YOUR SPEECH
BEFORE, OKAY?

1466
01:04:13,060 --> 01:04:16,070
<i>I KNOW WHAT IT IS --
YOU WORKED HARD, YOUR
FATHER WORKED HARD,</i>

1467
01:04:16,060 --> 01:04:18,060
<i>AND THEREFORE,
I <i>HAVE TO WORK HARD.</i>

1468
01:04:18,070 --> 01:04:19,570
OKAY.

1469
01:04:20,070 --> 01:04:21,570
I WANT TO WORK HARD, POP!

1470
01:04:21,570 --> 01:04:25,580
I WANT TO WORK HARD AT SCHOOL
TO GET A GOOD JOB.

1471
01:04:25,570 --> 01:04:26,570
ALL RIGHT!

1472
01:04:26,580 --> 01:04:28,580
I'VE HAD ENOUGH.
ALL RIGHT?

1473
01:04:28,580 --> 01:04:31,080
I DIDN'T SPEND MY DAY
AT THE BEACH, ALL RIGHT?

1474
01:04:31,080 --> 01:04:33,080
<i>I'M TIRED.</i>

1475
01:04:33,080 --> 01:04:36,590
<i>I DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT THIS ANYMORE.</i>

1476
01:04:36,590 --> 01:04:38,090
YOU HAVE NO IDEA --

1477
01:04:38,090 --> 01:04:41,090
WHAT DID I SAY?!

1478
01:04:43,590 --> 01:04:45,600
MOM?

1479
01:04:47,100 --> 01:04:50,100
<i>MOM, PLEASE SAY SOMETHING
TO HIM.</i>

1480
01:04:50,100 --> 01:04:52,100
<i>MOM!</i>

1481
01:04:52,100 --> 01:04:53,600
HUH?

1482
01:04:56,690 --> 01:04:58,610
<i>Woman on P.A.: DR. FISCHBEIN,
PLEASE DIAL THE OPERATOR.</i>

1483
01:04:58,610 --> 01:05:01,110
WHY DON'T WE GO
DISCUSS THIS IN PRIVATE?

1484
01:05:01,110 --> 01:05:02,610
<i>Mrs. Jacobsen:
JUST TELL US.</i>

1485
01:05:05,110 --> 01:05:07,110
HIS WHITE-BLOOD COUNT
IS HIGH.

1486
01:05:07,620 --> 01:05:10,620
AND MOST OF THE CELLS
THAT I CAN SEE IN HIS BLOOD

1487
01:05:10,620 --> 01:05:12,620
ARE LEUKEMIA CELLS.

1488
01:05:12,620 --> 01:05:14,630
I'M SO SORRY.

1489
01:05:14,620 --> 01:05:16,620
WHAT'S THE PROGNOSIS?

1490
01:05:16,630 --> 01:05:18,630
DANNY'S BEEN ON ARA-C
BEFORE,

1491
01:05:18,630 --> 01:05:21,130
BUT THIS TIME, WE'RE GIVING
HIM A MUCH HIGHER DOSAGE.

1492
01:05:21,130 --> 01:05:24,640
IT'S GOING TO ALLOW US
TO HAVE A FIGHTING CHANCE

1493
01:05:24,630 --> 01:05:27,130
TO GET HIM
BACK INTO REMISSION.

1494
01:05:27,140 --> 01:05:30,640
BUT...I WOULDN'T BE
COMPLETELY HONEST
IF I DIDN'T TELL YOU

1495
01:05:30,640 --> 01:05:32,640
THAT HIS CHANCES FOR SURVIVAL
ARE VERY LOW.

1496
01:05:38,150 --> 01:05:41,150
[ Deep voice ] ANOTHER STRIKEOUT
FOR SEAMUS'S TEAM.

1497
01:05:41,150 --> 01:05:43,650
PETE'S TEAM, TRYING TO BE
THE FIRST TEAM EVER

1498
01:05:43,650 --> 01:05:46,160
IN THE HISTORY OF BASEBALL
TO GO UNDEFEATED,

1499
01:05:46,150 --> 01:05:49,150
COMES TO BAT
WITH A 13-RUN LEAD.

1500
01:05:49,160 --> 01:05:51,660
[ Higher voice ] JACK,
THEY'RE NOT ONLY UNDEFEATED,

1501
01:05:51,660 --> 01:05:55,170
BUT THEY'VE 10-RUN-RULED
EVERY SINGLE TEAM
THEY'VE PLAYED.

1502
01:05:55,160 --> 01:05:56,660
<i>[ Deep voice ]
GOOD POINT, CHARLIE.</i>

1503
01:05:57,170 --> 01:05:58,670
[ SPINNER WHIRRING ]

1504
01:05:58,670 --> 01:06:00,670
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

1505
01:06:00,670 --> 01:06:02,670
<i>WHAT ARE YOU <i>DOING HERE?</i>

1506
01:06:02,670 --> 01:06:06,180
WE HAVE TO COMPLETE
THE DECATHLON.

1507
01:06:06,170 --> 01:06:07,170
WE CAN'T.

1508
01:06:07,680 --> 01:06:10,680
WE HAVE TO.
I KNOW I CAN DO IT.

1509
01:06:10,680 --> 01:06:13,180
LISTEN, I'M GROUNDED <i>FOREVER
BECAUSE OF YOU.</i>

1510
01:06:13,180 --> 01:06:16,690
IF MY DAD SAW ME WITH YOU,
I'D BE GROUNDED TO <i>INFINITY.</i>

1511
01:06:16,690 --> 01:06:18,690
NO, <i>I'D BE GROUNDED
TO INFINITY</i>

1512
01:06:18,690 --> 01:06:20,690
IF MY PARENTS KNEW
I WAS HERE.

1513
01:06:20,690 --> 01:06:22,190
THEY THINK I'M NAPPING.

1514
01:06:22,190 --> 01:06:25,200
LISTEN,
I...CAN'T...DO IT!

1515
01:06:25,190 --> 01:06:26,190
NO, <i>YOU LISTEN.</i>

1516
01:06:26,700 --> 01:06:28,700
THIS MIGHT BE MY LAST CHANCE
FOR A WHILE.

1517
01:06:28,700 --> 01:06:32,200
<i>THEY MIGHT PUT ME ON CHEMO
RIGHT AWAY.</i>

1518
01:06:32,200 --> 01:06:34,210
THE TESTS ARE BAD.

1519
01:06:34,200 --> 01:06:36,700
[ SIGHS ] I'M NOT GONNA
DISOBEY MY DAD AGAIN.

1520
01:06:36,710 --> 01:06:40,210
I GOTTA BE ABLE TO
TELL MY PARENTS THAT
I'M GOING TO HEAVEN.

1521
01:06:40,210 --> 01:06:41,210
YOU CAN'T GO TO HEAVEN.

1522
01:06:41,710 --> 01:06:43,710
IT'S OUT-OF-BOUNDS
AND OFF-LIMITS TO JEWS.

1523
01:06:43,710 --> 01:06:46,720
THERE'S NOTHING THAT
YOU OR I COULD DO ABOUT IT.

1524
01:06:46,720 --> 01:06:49,220
YOU SAID IF I FINISHED
THE DECATHLON,

1525
01:06:49,220 --> 01:06:51,720
<i>I'M GOING TO HEAVEN!
WELL, I WAS WRONG.</i>

1526
01:06:53,720 --> 01:06:55,230
YOU GOTTA GET OUTTA HERE.

1527
01:06:55,220 --> 01:06:57,720
I'M GONNA GET IN SO MUCH
TROUBLE BECAUSE OF YOU,

1528
01:06:57,730 --> 01:07:00,230
AND THEN I'M GOING TO HELL
FOR SURE.

1529
01:07:00,230 --> 01:07:02,230
Get outta here.

1530
01:07:10,240 --> 01:07:12,240
THAT WAS A BRIEF RAIN DELAY.

1531
01:07:12,240 --> 01:07:15,250
PETE'S TEAM COMES TO BAT.

1532
01:08:01,460 --> 01:08:04,460
[ DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE ]

1533
01:08:04,960 --> 01:08:06,460
<i>HONEY...</i>

1534
01:08:06,460 --> 01:08:08,470
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE GONNA SAY,
AND FORGET IT.

1535
01:08:08,460 --> 01:08:10,460
MY DECISION ABOUT THIS
IS FINAL.

1536
01:08:10,470 --> 01:08:12,470
YOU KNOW, JOSEPH, WHEN
FATHER MURPHY MARRIED US --

1537
01:08:12,970 --> 01:08:15,970
OH, DON'T START
WITH THAT CRAP.

1538
01:08:15,970 --> 01:08:16,970
HE SAID --

1539
01:08:16,970 --> 01:08:19,480
<i>FATHER MURPHY
WAS AN IDIOT.</i>

1540
01:08:19,970 --> 01:08:22,470
CAN YOU STOP TALKING
FOR ONE SECOND, JOE?

1541
01:08:22,480 --> 01:08:26,480
I'VE JUST GOT SOMETHING
TO SAY, AND I DON'T WANT
YOU TO INTERRUPT ME, OKAY?

1542
01:08:26,480 --> 01:08:30,990
I'M NOT GONNA ALLOW YOU
TO TAKE AWAY PATRICK'S CHANCE.

1543
01:08:30,990 --> 01:08:34,990
HE'S GONNA PURSUE
THIS DREAM, JOE.

1544
01:08:34,990 --> 01:08:37,490
THE RABBI'S BEING GENEROUS,
AND I THINK THAT...

1545
01:08:37,490 --> 01:08:40,000
I THINK YOU THINK
IT REFLECTS POORLY ON YOU.

1546
01:08:39,990 --> 01:08:41,490
NO, NO, NO, NO.
IT'S NOT ABOUT THAT.

1547
01:08:42,000 --> 01:08:43,500
<i>HONEY, YES, IT IS.
IT --</i>

1548
01:08:43,500 --> 01:08:46,000
<i>YOU CAN'T AFFORD TO SEND
YOUR CHILDREN TO COLLEGE,</i>

1549
01:08:46,000 --> 01:08:47,500
<i>SO YOU'VE DECIDED
IT'S A BAD THING.</i>

1550
01:08:48,000 --> 01:08:49,000
I'M NOT GONNA STAND BY

1551
01:08:49,000 --> 01:08:51,500
AND LET YOU SQUASH
PATRICK'S DREAMS.

1552
01:08:51,510 --> 01:08:53,010
IT'S JUST
NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

1553
01:08:53,010 --> 01:08:55,510
IT'S NOT ABOUT DREAMS.

1554
01:08:55,510 --> 01:08:58,020
<i>WHAT'S IT ABOUT, JOE?
TELL ME WHAT IT'S ABOUT.</i>

1555
01:08:58,010 --> 01:08:59,010
IT'S ABOUT WHAT'S RIGHT.

1556
01:08:59,510 --> 01:09:01,510
PATRICK KNEW THAT
IF HE WAS GONNA GO TO COLLEGE,

1557
01:09:01,520 --> 01:09:03,020
HE WAS GONNA <i>EARN IT</i>

1558
01:09:03,020 --> 01:09:05,520
BY GETTING GOOD GRADES
AND EARNING A SCHOLARSHIP.

1559
01:09:05,520 --> 01:09:07,520
<i>OH, YOU WANTED HIM
TO TAKE SCHOOL SERIOUSLY?</i>

1560
01:09:08,020 --> 01:09:10,020
<i>YEAH.
IS THAT WHAT HE LEARNED
FROM YOU?</i>

1561
01:09:10,020 --> 01:09:11,520
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

1562
01:09:11,530 --> 01:09:13,030
"OH, HE'S JUST GONNA
GO GET A CITY JOB.

1563
01:09:13,530 --> 01:09:15,030
"WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES COLLEGE MAKE?

1564
01:09:15,030 --> 01:09:16,530
IT DOESN'T MATTER
IF HE GETS A's OR C's."

1565
01:09:16,530 --> 01:09:18,040
BUT THAT WASN'T GOOD ENOUGH
FOR HIM.

1566
01:09:18,030 --> 01:09:20,530
HE WOKE UP ONE DAY
AND SAID, "I HAVE TO BE
BETTER THAN THAT."

1567
01:09:20,540 --> 01:09:24,540
<i>AND YOU KNOW, <i>HE'S
GOTTEN STRAIGHT A's
EVER SINCE THAT DAY,</i>

1568
01:09:24,540 --> 01:09:27,040
<i>'CAUSE HE'S A CHIP
OFF THE OLD BLOCK,</i>

1569
01:09:27,040 --> 01:09:30,050
<i>AND HE WANTS TO DO HIS BEST
AT WHATEVER HE DOES.</i>

1570
01:09:30,040 --> 01:09:32,540
<i>AND THAT'S WHAT HE'S
GONNA DO -- IN COLLEGE,</i>

1571
01:09:32,550 --> 01:09:36,550
WITH THE SCHOLARSHIP HE ACCEPTS
<i>FROM RABBI JACOBSEN.</i>

1572
01:09:36,550 --> 01:09:38,060
THAT'S RIGHT, JOE.

1573
01:09:38,050 --> 01:09:41,050
OR SO HELP ME GOD, WHEN
YOU COME AT HOME AT NIGHT,

1574
01:09:41,060 --> 01:09:44,560
THE ONLY THING COLDER THAN
YOUR FOOD WILL BE YOUR BED.

1575
01:09:47,560 --> 01:09:50,070
[ DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE ]

1576
01:09:54,070 --> 01:09:55,570
IS PATRICK GETTING
A NEW JOB?

1577
01:09:55,570 --> 01:09:57,070
<i>[ LAUGHS ]
LISTEN TO YOU --</i>

1578
01:09:57,570 --> 01:09:59,580
ALWAYS WORRIED ABOUT
EVERYONE ELSE'S BUSINESS.

1579
01:09:59,570 --> 01:10:02,070
YOU GET THAT FROM MY SIDE
OF THE FAMILY, YOU KNOW.

1580
01:10:02,080 --> 01:10:05,080
YEAH, DAD SAID I GOT
A LOT OF THINGS FROM
YOUR SIDE OF THE FAMILY.

1581
01:10:05,080 --> 01:10:06,080
<i>OH, HE DID, DID HE?</i>

1582
01:10:06,080 --> 01:10:07,580
YOU KNOW WHAT HE MEANS?

1583
01:10:08,080 --> 01:10:11,080
YOUR SWEETNESS, YOUR HUMOR,
AND DEFINITELY YOUR NOSE.

1584
01:10:14,090 --> 01:10:18,100
MOM, DO YOU THINK DAD
WILL END MY GROUNDING SOON?

1585
01:10:18,090 --> 01:10:19,590
WELL, THAT DEPENDS.

1586
01:10:19,590 --> 01:10:23,090
ARE YOU TRULY SORRY
FOR DISOBEYING HIM,
LYING TO ME?

1587
01:10:23,100 --> 01:10:27,100
MOM, I WAS ON A QUEST,
AND ON QUESTS, YOU
HAVE TO TAKE RISKS.

1588
01:10:27,100 --> 01:10:30,110
YOU KNOW WHAT, HONEY --
YOU KNOW THAT FEELING
YOU GET IN YOUR HEART,

1589
01:10:30,100 --> 01:10:31,600
THAT LITTLE VOICE
THAT TALKS TO YOU?

1590
01:10:31,610 --> 01:10:33,610
<i>YOU KNOW WHY THAT'S THERE?</i>

1591
01:10:33,610 --> 01:10:35,610
<i>IT'S BECAUSE
I CAN'T ALWAYS BE WITH YOU</i>

1592
01:10:35,610 --> 01:10:37,610
TO TELL YOU WHAT'S RIGHT
AND WHAT'S WRONG.

1593
01:10:37,610 --> 01:10:39,120
THAT'S YOUR CONSCIENCE.

1594
01:10:39,110 --> 01:10:43,610
<i>WHAT DOES YOUR CONSCIENCE SAY
TO YOU ABOUT YOUR QUEST?</i>

1595
01:10:44,120 --> 01:10:48,130
I THINK IT SAYS TO DO
WHAT YOU AND DAD TELL ME TO DO.

1596
01:10:48,120 --> 01:10:50,120
WELL, THAT AND...

1597
01:10:50,120 --> 01:10:54,620
YOU KNOW WHAT? I BELIEVE
YOUR QUEST IS GOOD.

1598
01:10:54,630 --> 01:10:56,130
BUT DAD SAID --

1599
01:10:56,630 --> 01:11:00,140
<i>DADS DON'T ALWAYS KNOW...
EVERYTHING ALL THE TIME.</i>

1600
01:11:00,130 --> 01:11:01,630
JUST SOMETIMES.

1601
01:11:01,640 --> 01:11:05,140
THAT'S EASY FOR <i>YOU TO SAY.
HE CAN'T GROUND YOU.</i>

1602
01:11:05,640 --> 01:11:07,140
MNH-MNH.

1603
01:11:07,140 --> 01:11:10,150
WELL...DON'T GIVE UP
YOUR QUEST, HONEY.

1604
01:11:10,140 --> 01:11:12,140
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

1605
01:11:18,820 --> 01:11:19,820
COME ON IN.

1606
01:11:19,820 --> 01:11:21,330
PATRICK.
<i>HI.</i>

1607
01:11:21,320 --> 01:11:22,820
HOW YOU DOING?
I'M ALL RIGHT.

1608
01:11:23,320 --> 01:11:24,820
GOOD, GOOD.
WHERE'S YOUR DAD?

1609
01:11:24,830 --> 01:11:27,830
UH, HE, UH, HE HAD TO GO
RUN SOME ERRANDS.

1610
01:11:27,830 --> 01:11:30,330
HE'LL PICK ME UP HERE
IN A FEW MINUTES.

1611
01:11:30,330 --> 01:11:31,340
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

1612
01:11:31,830 --> 01:11:34,330
UH...LISTEN,
SINCE WE SPOKE ON THE PHONE,

1613
01:11:34,340 --> 01:11:36,840
I'VE RECEIVED A CALL
FROM THE HOSPITAL,

1614
01:11:36,840 --> 01:11:38,340
AND I'M NEEDED THERE.

1615
01:11:38,340 --> 01:11:40,340
MY WIFE...
[ SIGHS ] CALLED.

1616
01:11:40,340 --> 01:11:43,350
DANNY'S, UH, GOT AN INFECTION
FROM THE CHEMOTHERAPY,

1617
01:11:43,850 --> 01:11:46,350
SO I-I DON'T -- I DON'T HAVE
AS MUCH TIME TO...

1618
01:11:46,850 --> 01:11:50,350
TALK ABOUT THIS AS I, UH,
<i>AS WE HAD PLANNED.</i>

1619
01:11:50,850 --> 01:11:54,360
I, UM...
I HOPE EVERYTHING IS OKAY.

1620
01:11:54,360 --> 01:11:55,860
YEAH, WELL, ME TOO.

1621
01:11:55,860 --> 01:11:57,360
I, UH...I DON'T KNOW.

1622
01:11:57,360 --> 01:12:00,360
UH, HE'S HAD INFECTIONS
BEFORE, YOU KNOW?

1623
01:12:00,860 --> 01:12:01,870
<i>I'M SORRY.</i>

1624
01:12:01,860 --> 01:12:02,860
THANKS.

1625
01:12:03,360 --> 01:12:04,860
UH, UH,
REGARDING THE SCHOLARSHIP,

1626
01:12:04,870 --> 01:12:07,870
UH, I HOPE YOU REALIZE THAT
THIS IS...GONNA OPEN DOORS

1627
01:12:07,870 --> 01:12:10,370
THAT WOULD NEVER POSSIBLY
BE AVAILABLE TO YOU

1628
01:12:10,370 --> 01:12:11,880
WITHOUT A DEGREE.

1629
01:12:11,870 --> 01:12:13,370
<i>YEAH, I KNOW IT WILL.</i>

1630
01:12:13,370 --> 01:12:15,370
AND, UH...IF THE OFFER
IS STILL THERE,

1631
01:12:15,380 --> 01:12:18,380
I WOULD -- I WOULD
ABSOLUTELY LOVE A CHANCE --

1632
01:12:18,380 --> 01:12:20,880
OH, NO, NO, PATRICK,
THE SCHOLARSHIP IS YOURS.

1633
01:12:20,880 --> 01:12:23,390
ABSOLUTELY. YOU'RE GONNA
MAKE US ALL PROUD.

1634
01:12:23,380 --> 01:12:24,880
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

1635
01:12:24,890 --> 01:12:26,890
<i>YOU'RE GONNA MAKE
ESTHER SIMON PROUD.</i>

1636
01:12:26,890 --> 01:12:28,390
WOW. OHH.

1637
01:12:28,390 --> 01:12:30,890
AS I SAID, I JUST WISH
I HAD MORE TIME.

1638
01:12:30,890 --> 01:12:33,900
WE'LL WORK OUT ALL THE DETAILS
AT ANOTHER TIME.

1639
01:12:33,900 --> 01:12:35,900
UH, I WILL --
I WILL PRAY FOR DANNY.

1640
01:12:35,900 --> 01:12:37,400
THANK YOU.

1641
01:12:37,900 --> 01:12:39,900
<i>THANK YOU SO MUCH, RABBI.</i>

1642
01:12:39,900 --> 01:12:42,410
CONGRATULATIONS, PATRICK.

1643
01:13:03,930 --> 01:13:06,430
[ CRYING ]

1644
01:13:06,430 --> 01:13:08,430
SAVE MY SON.

1645
01:13:34,960 --> 01:13:36,960
<i>Announcer:
...CHET LEMON, FIRST SWING.</i>

1646
01:13:36,960 --> 01:13:38,960
COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON.
<i>STRIKE!</i>

1647
01:13:38,960 --> 01:13:42,470
OH, YOU SPINELESS
ROOKIE BUM!

1648
01:13:42,460 --> 01:13:43,960
<i>...THIRD TIME TODAY LOOKING,</i>

1649
01:13:43,970 --> 01:13:46,970
<i>AND PAUL RICHARDS HAS TO THINK
ABOUT SITTING YOUNG LEMON...</i>

1650
01:13:47,470 --> 01:13:48,470
HEY, POP?

1651
01:13:48,470 --> 01:13:49,470
[ MUTTERING ]

1652
01:13:49,970 --> 01:13:50,470
POP?

1653
01:13:50,970 --> 01:13:51,980
WHAT?

1654
01:13:51,970 --> 01:13:54,470
IF I'M GONNA GO TO COLLEGE,
I'M GONNA WORK MY ASS OFF.

1655
01:13:54,980 --> 01:13:58,480
I'M -- REALLY, I'M NOT GONNA
BE A POT-SMOKING,

1656
01:13:58,480 --> 01:14:00,480
SLEEP-TILL-NOON
COLLEGE HIPPIE.

1657
01:14:00,480 --> 01:14:03,490
<i>...FUNDAMENTAL BASEBALL GAME,
FOLKS...</i>

1658
01:14:03,480 --> 01:14:07,480
I'M GONNA DO THIS
COLLEGE THING, AND
I'M GONNA DO IT RIGHT.

1659
01:14:07,490 --> 01:14:09,990
<i>...LAMAR JOHNSON
COMING TO THE PLATE...</i>

1660
01:14:09,990 --> 01:14:12,500
I KNOW.

1661
01:14:12,490 --> 01:14:13,990
<i>...SOX ARE DOWN
BY THREE RUNS...</i>

1662
01:14:14,000 --> 01:14:15,500
I KNOW YOU ARE.

1663
01:14:15,500 --> 01:14:18,000
<i>RICHARDS JUST CAN'T SEEM
TO FIND A SPOT</i>

1664
01:14:18,000 --> 01:14:19,500
<i>IN THE EVERYDAY LINEUP
FOR HIM.</i>

1665
01:14:19,500 --> 01:14:22,010
<i>THE WHITE SOX'S YOUNG NUCLEUS
OF CHET LEMON,</i>

1666
01:14:22,000 --> 01:14:23,500
<i>LAMAR JOHNSON, JORGE ORTA...</i>

1667
01:14:23,500 --> 01:14:25,500
HEY...

1668
01:14:25,510 --> 01:14:28,010
<i>BUT BECK SEEMS TO THINK WITH
THESE YOUNG PLAYERS MATURING...</i>

1669
01:14:28,510 --> 01:14:32,520
DON'T BE ACTING LIKE THIS
IS YOUR FIRST TIME DRINKING.

1670
01:14:32,510 --> 01:14:33,510
COME ON.

1671
01:14:33,510 --> 01:14:36,010
<i>I DON'T KNOW.
SURE WOULD BE NICE...</i>

1672
01:14:36,020 --> 01:14:38,020
AND I DIDN'T GIVE THAT
TO YOU.

1673
01:14:38,020 --> 01:14:40,020
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

1674
01:14:40,020 --> 01:14:42,030
<i>Joe: HEY. PEDRO.</i>

1675
01:14:42,020 --> 01:14:43,520
HEY, DAD.

1676
01:14:43,520 --> 01:14:46,520
SEAMUS SAYS THERE'S
A BIG GAME OVER THERE

1677
01:14:46,530 --> 01:14:48,030
AT, UH, HOLY CROSS,

1678
01:14:48,030 --> 01:14:51,540
<i>AND, UH, THEY COULD PROBABLY
USE ANOTHER PLAYER.</i>

1679
01:14:51,530 --> 01:14:53,030
SO CAN I GO?

1680
01:14:53,030 --> 01:14:56,030
NO, NO, NO.
YOU'RE GROUNDED, REMEMBER?

1681
01:14:56,040 --> 01:14:57,540
<i>I'M GONNA GO PLAY,</i>

1682
01:14:57,540 --> 01:15:00,540
<i>AND I'M JUST LETTING YOU KNOW
WHERE I'M AT.</i>

1683
01:15:02,540 --> 01:15:05,040
OH, WAIT --
Y-YOU <i>WANT TO PLAY?</i>

1684
01:15:06,550 --> 01:15:08,050
<i>DO YOU WANT TO PLAY?</i>

1685
01:15:08,050 --> 01:15:09,050
CAN I?

1686
01:15:09,050 --> 01:15:11,560
[ LAUGHS ]
GO ON, GET OUTTA HERE.

1687
01:15:15,560 --> 01:15:18,060
SORRY, DAD.
I WON'T DISOBEY YOU AGAIN.

1688
01:15:20,560 --> 01:15:24,070
OH, LISTEN, PATRICK SAW
RABBI JACOBSEN LAST NIGHT.

1689
01:15:24,070 --> 01:15:26,570
I GUESS DANNY'S
BACK IN THE HOSPITAL.

1690
01:15:26,570 --> 01:15:31,070
YEAH, HE SAID THAT
HE THOUGHT THEY MIGHT
PUT HIM BACK THERE.

1691
01:15:31,070 --> 01:15:33,080
I HOPE HE'S OKAY.

1692
01:15:33,070 --> 01:15:35,070
MM-HMM.

1693
01:15:35,080 --> 01:15:37,580
YOU KNOW, IT'S TOUGH,
WHAT HE'S GOT.

1694
01:15:38,080 --> 01:15:40,580
IT'S TOUGH ON THE KID,
<i>AND, UH...</i>

1695
01:15:40,580 --> 01:15:43,590
IT'S GOTTA BE TOUGH
ON THE PARENTS, TOO.

1696
01:15:43,580 --> 01:15:45,580
WELL, I'LL PRAY FOR HIM.

1697
01:15:45,590 --> 01:15:48,590
OH, YEAH.
THAT'S A NICE IDEA.

1698
01:15:48,590 --> 01:15:50,090
<i>YEAH. GOOD.</i>

1699
01:15:50,090 --> 01:15:51,600
<i>OH, AND, UH...</i>

1700
01:15:52,090 --> 01:15:54,590
HE ALSO TOLD PATRICK
TO TELL YOU THAT, UH...

1701
01:15:54,600 --> 01:15:57,600
DANNY FINISHED
THE DECATHLON.

1702
01:15:57,600 --> 01:16:00,600
<i>71 STROKES THERE,
86 BACK.</i>

1703
01:16:00,600 --> 01:16:02,110
NO WAY!

1704
01:16:02,100 --> 01:16:03,100
YES WAY.

1705
01:16:03,100 --> 01:16:05,100
I DID IT IN 55 STROKES.

1706
01:16:05,610 --> 01:16:06,610
OH, YOU DID, HUH?

1707
01:16:07,110 --> 01:16:10,610
YEAH, BUT FOR HIS AGE AND SIZE,
71 STROKES IS GREAT.

1708
01:16:10,610 --> 01:16:13,120
I MEAN, HE FINISHED
THE DECATHLON.

1709
01:16:13,110 --> 01:16:15,610
<i>I CAN GIVE HIM HIS MEDAL
SO HE CAN GO TO HEAVEN.</i>

1710
01:16:15,620 --> 01:16:18,120
<i>YEAH.
SEE YOU LATER, DAD.</i>

1711
01:16:18,120 --> 01:16:21,120
ALL RIGHT, SEE YOU, PETE.

1712
01:16:26,130 --> 01:16:28,130
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

1713
01:16:41,140 --> 01:16:43,650
[ RUSTLING ]

1714
01:16:49,650 --> 01:16:51,150
MR. O'MALLEY.

1715
01:16:52,650 --> 01:16:54,650
<i>STEALING COMMUNION?</i>

1716
01:16:58,660 --> 01:17:00,160
FATHER KELLY.

1717
01:17:00,160 --> 01:17:02,670
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

1718
01:17:02,660 --> 01:17:05,160
<i>AND DON'T TELL ME
YOU'RE HUNGRY.</i>

1719
01:17:05,170 --> 01:17:07,170
NO, FATHER.
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

1720
01:17:07,170 --> 01:17:10,170
I HEAR THIS STUFF
ISN'T GOOD, ANYWAYS.

1721
01:17:10,170 --> 01:17:12,180
WELL, I WISH WE COULD CHANGE
BREAD DISTRIBUTORS,

1722
01:17:12,170 --> 01:17:13,670
BUT THAT'S NEITHER HERE
NOR THERE.

1723
01:17:14,180 --> 01:17:15,680
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
MR. O'MALLEY?

1724
01:17:17,180 --> 01:17:20,180
I'VE GOT A FRIEND WHO
REALLY NEEDS A PIECE OF JESUS.

1725
01:17:20,180 --> 01:17:23,690
<i>HE'S REALLY SICK,
AND HE'S IN THE HOSPITAL.</i>

1726
01:17:23,680 --> 01:17:25,180
AHH.

1727
01:17:25,190 --> 01:17:29,190
WE HAVE PEOPLE WHO GIVE
COMMUNION TO THE SICK
IN THE HOSPITAL.

1728
01:17:29,190 --> 01:17:32,700
BUT...THEY CAN'T GIVE IT
TO <i>HIM.</i>

1729
01:17:32,690 --> 01:17:34,190
WHY NOT?

1730
01:17:34,200 --> 01:17:37,200
BECAUSE HE'S NOT CATHOLIC,
<i>AND HE'S ONLY 7.</i>

1731
01:17:37,200 --> 01:17:38,700
YOUR FRIEND --
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

1732
01:17:38,700 --> 01:17:40,200
DANNY.
<i>DANNY.</i>

1733
01:17:40,200 --> 01:17:43,710
<i>WELL, THAT POSES A BIT
OF A PROBLEM, MR. O'MALLEY.</i>

1734
01:17:43,700 --> 01:17:47,700
COMMUNION IS FOR CHRISTIANS
WHO HAVE EARNED THE RIGHT

1735
01:17:47,710 --> 01:17:50,710
TO RECEIVE JESUS
AND WHO ARE OF AGE.

1736
01:17:50,710 --> 01:17:53,220
OH, HE'S EARNED THE RIGHT.
HE'S PASSED ALL THE TESTS.

1737
01:17:53,210 --> 01:17:54,710
TESTS? WHAT TESTS?

1738
01:17:54,720 --> 01:17:57,720
THE TESTS WE MADE UP TO SEE
IF HE'S WORTHY OF JESUS.

1739
01:17:58,220 --> 01:17:59,720
AND HE IS WORTHY,
ALL RIGHT.

1740
01:17:59,720 --> 01:18:02,230
HE'S AS WORTHY
AS ANY CATHOLIC I KNOW.

1741
01:18:02,220 --> 01:18:04,720
WELL, I-I BELIEVE YOU,
MR. O'MALLEY.

1742
01:18:04,730 --> 01:18:05,730
BUT WE'RE CATHOLICS.

1743
01:18:06,230 --> 01:18:08,230
WE -- WE HAVE
THESE TRADITIONS.

1744
01:18:08,230 --> 01:18:10,730
<i>WELL, JUST BECAUSE
HE'S NOT OLD ENOUGH,</i>

1745
01:18:10,730 --> 01:18:12,240
THAT TRADITION'S NOT FAIR,

1746
01:18:12,230 --> 01:18:15,230
BECAUSE HE MAY NOT LIVE
LONG ENOUGH TO BE OLD ENOUGH.

1747
01:18:15,240 --> 01:18:19,240
AND IF JESUS DIDN'T WANT HIM
TO HAVE A PART OF HIM JUST
BECAUSE HE'S NOT OLD ENOUGH,

1748
01:18:19,240 --> 01:18:23,250
WELL, THAT DOESN'T SEEM LIKE
THE JESUS <i>I KNOW.</i>

1749
01:18:27,250 --> 01:18:30,250
THAT BREAD, UH...

1750
01:18:30,250 --> 01:18:31,760
<i>IS UNCONSECRATED.</i>

1751
01:18:31,750 --> 01:18:33,750
<i>IT'S -- IT'S NOT
THE BODY OF CHRIST.</i>

1752
01:18:33,750 --> 01:18:35,250
<i>IT'S JUST BREAD.</i>

1753
01:18:35,260 --> 01:18:39,760
IT DOESN'T MATTER.
JESUS WON'T MIND.

1754
01:18:41,760 --> 01:18:44,260
GO AHEAD. TAKE THE HOST
TO YOUR FRIEND.

1755
01:18:44,770 --> 01:18:45,770
<i>GO ON.</i>

1756
01:18:45,770 --> 01:18:47,770
THANKS, FATHER.

1757
01:18:51,270 --> 01:18:53,280
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

1758
01:19:32,810 --> 01:19:35,310
<i>Woman on P.A.:
DR. DANNON TO PEDIATRICS.</i>

1759
01:19:35,820 --> 01:19:39,320
<i>DR. DANNON TO PEDIATRICS,
STAT.</i>

1760
01:19:44,330 --> 01:19:45,330
[ SIGHS ]

1761
01:19:48,830 --> 01:19:50,830
SEE YOU LATER.
ALL RIGHT.

1762
01:19:50,830 --> 01:19:52,340
RABBI?

1763
01:19:52,330 --> 01:19:53,330
PETE.

1764
01:19:53,330 --> 01:19:56,330
RABBI,
I NEED TO SEE DANNY.

1765
